<text name="event_ALISON_DEFECTOR_c1_c2_choice">Reject his offer. You can never trust these Rebels. [ Rbl SF DR | 1 Boarder, Rbl SF DR | Second chance ]</text>
<text name="event_ALISON_DEFECTOR_HELP_1_text">The dishonorable Rebel has deceived you. He damages your engines and steals your flight data before teleporting away. The fleet will be able to track you with ease. If they can't kill you now, that is! [ Rbl SF DR; S: 0.5, 2-3, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_ALISON_DEFECTOR_HELP_2_2_text">Your new crew-member smiles, then reveals a small remote trigger in the palm of his hand. Explosions rocket around the ship as more intruders teleport aboard! [ Rbl SF DR; S: 0.5, 2-3, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_ALISON_DEFECTOR_HELP_2_3_text">Relieved and light-headed, your new crewmember gets to work as the Rebel ship attacks. [ Rbl SF DR; S: 0.5, 2-3, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_ALISON_DEFECTOR_HELP_2_6_text">The Rebel makes to take his assigned station, then suddenly turns and eviscerates the nearest crew-member. Red Alert! [ Rbl SF DR; 1 Human Boarder; S: 0.5, 2-3, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_ALISON_DEFECTOR_REJECT_3_c1_choice">Reluctantly accept his proposal and fight the Rebel ship. [ -3 Hull, Rbl SF DR, Fleet+ | -3 Hull, 2 Human Boarders, Rbl SF DR | x3 HumanCrew+, Quest, Rbl SF DR | 1 HumanBoarder, Rbl SF DR, Crew- (CB+) ]</text>
<text name="event_ALISON_DEFECTOR_REJECT_3_c2_choice">Reject him outright and execute him on the spot. [ Rbl SF DR; S: 0.5, 2-3, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_ALISON_DEFECTOR_REJECT_3_c3_choice">Reject his offer again. [ Rbl SF DR, 1 Human Boarder; S: 0.5, 2-3, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_ALISON_MANTIS_CREW_c1_c1_choice">Side with the fugitive and fight the Engi ship. [ -5 Hull, SF DR | MantisCrew+, Eng SF DR ]</text>
<text name="event_ALISON_MANTIS_CREW_c1_c2_choice">Agree to offer up the Mantis in exchange for a bounty. [ HScrap | -5 Hull, HScrap | 1 Mantis Boarder, Eng SF DR w/Mantis crew ]</text>
<text name="event_ASTEROID_DERELICT_SHIP_ROCK_1_c1_c1_choice">Take the weapon and any spare scrap. [ LScrapWeapon ]</text>
<text name="event_ASTEROID_DERELICT_SHIP_ROCK_1_c1_c2_choice">Grab the stasis chamber. [ LScrap, StasisPod Augment ]</text>
<text name="event_ASTEROID_DERELICT_SHIP_SEARCH_3_c1_c1_choice">Take the weapon and any spare scrap. [ LScrapWeapon ]</text>
<text name="event_ASTEROID_DERELICT_SHIP_SEARCH_3_c1_c2_choice">Grab the stasis chamber. [ LScrap, StasisPod Augment ]</text>
<text name="event_ASTEROID_DERELICT_SHIP_c1_choice">Search for the ship. [ -5 Hull | RStd | LScrapWeapon or LScrap Stasis Pod ]</text>
<text name="event_ASTEROID_DERELICT_SHIP_c2_choice">Avoid the area. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_ASTEROID_DERELICT_SHIP_c3_choice">(Rock Plating) Make a thorough search for the ship without fear of stray asteroids. [ LScrapWeapon or LScrap Stasis Pod ]</text>
<text name="event_ASTEROID_EXPLORE_c1_choice">Explore the asteroid field. [ Nil | HScrapFuel | MScrapMiss | MScrapDrones | -5 Hull | Prt SF DR w/Asteroids; Esc: 0.5, 2-4; S: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_ASTEROID_EXPLORE_c2_choice">Too dangerous. We'll just wait for the FTL to charge. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_ASTEROID_EXPLORE_c3_choice">(Scrap Recovery Arm) Attempt to mine the asteroids. [ HScrap ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_ASTEROID_text">You arrive in an asteroid belt to discover that a Rebel automated-scout has been stationed here. Prepare for a fight! [ Auto SF DR w/Asteroids ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_SUN_text">You arrive at the beacon to find yourself dangerously close to a star. An automated Rebel ship, impervious to the heat, moves in to engage. [ Auto SF DR w/Solar-flare ]</text>
<text name="event_BOARDERS_ASTEROID_GHOST_c1_choice">Prepare for a fight! [ 3-6 Boarders w/asteroids ]</text>
<text name="event_BOARDERS_ASTEROID_GHOST_c2_choice">(Engines) Activate full impulse drive to escape. [ -4 Hull ]</text>
<text name="event_BOARDERS_ASTEROID_GHOST_c3_choice">(Piloting) Have your pilot maneuver you out of the asteroid field. [ 2-4 Boarders ]</text>
<text name="event_CIVILIAN_ASTEROIDS_BEACON_2_c1_choice">Try to shield their ship with yours. [ -1 Hull, HScrapFuel | LScrap | -4 Hull, LScrap ]</text>
<text name="event_CIVILIAN_ASTEROIDS_BEACON_2_c2_choice">Don't risk our ship. Leave them to their fate. [ Nil | Fleet+1 ]</text>
<text name="event_CIVILIAN_ASTEROIDS_BEACON_2_c3_choice">(Defense Drone) Use a Defense Drone to protect their ship. [ -1 Drone, [ Hidden Federation Base Quest | -4 Hull, MScrapWeapon ] ]</text>
<text name="event_CIVILIAN_ASTEROIDS_BEACON_2_c4_choice">(Repair Drone) Send a Repair Drone to fix their Shields. [ -1 Drone, [ Hidden Federation Base Quest | -4 Hull, MScrapWeapon ] ]</text>
<text name="event_CIVILIAN_ASTEROIDS_BEACON_2_c5_choice">(Teleporter) Offer to beam them aboard your ship. [ Crew+ | [ HScrap | MScrap | +10 Hull ] ]</text>
<text name="event_CIVILIAN_ASTEROIDS_BEACON_2_c6_choice">(Rock Armor) Shield their ship with yours and escort them out. [ MScrapFuel ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_INFESTATION_c1_choice">Send the crew to help! Giant alien spiders are no joke. [ Crew- CB+ | HStuff ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_INFESTATION_c2_choice">Leave them alone. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_INFESTATION_c3_choice">(Anti-Personnel Drone) Send your battle drone in to help. [ -1 Drone, MStuff ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_INFESTATION_c4_choice">(Boarding Drone) Launch a Boarding drone into the station. [ -1 Drone, LStd ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_INFESTATION_c5_choice">(Bio Beam) Use the beam to pick off the spiders. [ HStuff ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_SATELLITE_DEFENSE_c1_c1_choice">Simply fire on the defense system from a distance. [ LStd | -5 Hull ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_SATELLITE_DEFENSE_c1_c2_choice">(Ion Weapon) Disable the defense system. [ HStd ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_SATELLITE_DEFENSE_c1_c3_choice">(Cloaking) Use your Cloaking to disable the system. [ LStd ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_SATELLITE_DEFENSE_c1_c4_choice">(Improved Cloaking) Use your Cloaking to disable the system. [ MStd ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_SATELLITE_DEFENSE_c1_c5_choice">(Advanced Cloaking) Use your Cloaking to disable the system. [ HStd ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_SATELLITE_DEFENSE_c1_c6_choice">(Engi Crew) Remotely repair its targeting system. [ HStd ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_SATELLITE_DEFENSE_c1_choice">Promise to help. [ LStd | -5 Hull | Ion/Cloak/Engi BOs ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_SATELLITE_DEFENSE_c2_choice">Leave them alone. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_STATION_DISEASE_c1_choice">Send in your crew to help control the crowds. [ Nil | Crew- (CB-), MStuff ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_STATION_DISEASE_c2_choice">Ignore their request and move on. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_STATION_DISEASE_c3_choice">(Rock Crew) Send your Rock crew-member to prevent a riot. [ MStuff ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_STATION_DISEASE_c4_choice">(Engi Crew) Send your Engi to calm down the infected. [ MStuff ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_STATION_DISEASE_c5_choice">(Adv. Medbay) Use your Medbay to help synthesize a cure. [ MStuff | HScrapWeapon w/MedBots BO ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_STATION_DISEASE_c5_c2_choice">(Engi Med-bot Dispersal) Use the Nano med-bots to accelerate the dispersal of the cure. [ HScrapWeapon ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_STATION_FIRE_c1_choice">Send your crew in a shuttle to help put out the fire. [ Crew- CB+, LScrap | HScrap ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_STATION_FIRE_c2_choice">Dock and try to rescue the survivors. [ -4 Hull, LScrap | Crew+, LScrap ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_STATION_FIRE_c3_choice">Leave. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_STATION_FIRE_c4_choice">(Rock Crew) Send your Rock crew-member in. [ HScrapAugment ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_STATION_FIRE_c5_choice">(Repair Drone) Send your Repair drone into the fire. [ HScrapDrone ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_TRAPPED_MINER_c1_choice">Try to dislodge the ship by shooting at the rocks. [ -2 Hull, LScrap | MStd ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_TRAPPED_MINER_c2_choice">Destroy and loot the ship. They're just pirates. [ MStd | Prt SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_TRAPPED_MINER_c3_choice">(Beam Weapon) Carefully cut the ship out. [ MStd ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_TRAPPED_MINER_c4_choice">(Beam Drone) Have your drone cut the ship out. [ -1 Drone, MStd ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_TRAPPED_MINER_LOOT_2_text">You decide the pirate is not worth saving and fire a few volleys into their hull. Before you can scrap the remains another pirate ship flashes on your radar. Perhaps they saw your deed, or perhaps they want to claim the spoils for themselves, but for whatever reason, they're charging weapons! [ Prt SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_DONOR_BLACK_RAVEN_c1_c1_choice">Accept his challenge. [ Slg SF K: MStd; CK: HStd; S: 0, 3-4, HScrapWeapon ]</text>
<text name="event_DONOR_BLACK_RAVEN_c1_c2_choice">Decline. [ Slg SF K: MStd; CK: HStd; S: 0, 3-4, HScrapWeapon ]</text>
<text name="event_DONOR_BLACK_RAVEN_c1_c3_choice">(Slugman Crew) Engage in a duel of the mind. [ HScrapWeapon | Slg SF 1-2 Boarders; K: MStd; CK: HStd; S: 0, 3-4, HScrapWeapon ]</text>
<text name="event_DONOR_MANTIS_CHASE_text">You are immediately hailed by an impressive looking Mantis ship, "Your ship would make a mighty fine prize. Prepare for battle!" [ Mts SF K: MStd, CK: HStd, Esc: 5-5, 5s, Mantis Chase Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_DONOR_MANTIS_CHASE2_c1_text">"Not YOU again! Do you know how much these repairs are going to cost me? Time to take out the big guns." [ Mts SF K: MStd Weapon; CK: HStd Weapon; S: 2-2, HWeap; Esc: 6-6, 12s, HStd ]</text>
<text name="event_DONOR_PONY_c1_c1_choice">Try to communicate peacefully. [ EngiCrew+,  LStd | Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_DONOR_PONY_c1_c2_choice">Bring some of the creatures on board to sell. [ Nil | Crew- (CB+) ]</text>
<text name="event_DONOR_PONY_c1_c3_choice">Leave. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_DONOR_PONY_c1_c4_choice">(Slugman Crew) Attempt to communicate telepathically. [ EngiCrew+ ]</text>
<text name="event_DONOR_PONY_c1_choice">Investigate. [ More... ]</text>
<text name="event_DONOR_PONY_c2_choice">Ignore it. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_DONOR_PLAGUE_c1_choice">Board the station and look for survivors. [ LScrap | LScrap, HumanCrew+ | LScrap, Crew- (CB-), LVL 2 Medbay will revive) ]</text>
<text name="event_DONOR_PLAGUE_c2_choice">Scrap some of the debris. [ RScrap ]</text>
<text name="event_ESCORT_BEACON_c1_choice">Lead them to their destination. [ LScrap, Ship Escort Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_ESCORT_BEACON_c2_choice">Decline. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_ESCORT_BEACON_c3_choice">(Advanced FTL Navigation) Have your navigation software calculate and upload route instructions to their ship. [ HStd ]</text>
<text name="event_FEDERATION_BASE_ASSIST_1_text">You arrive in the sector to see a small outpost being bombarded by an automated drone. This must be the Federation base you were told about! [ Auto SF K: LStd, DB: [ LScrapWeapon, Crew+ | HStd, +7 Hull ] ]</text>
<text name="event_FEDERATION_PLANET_SIGNAL_c1_choice">Send an away party to investigate. [ Hidden Federation Base Quest | MStuff, Federation Base Assist Quest | Nil | HStd | Rbl SF DR; 2-3 Human Boarders; S: 0.5, 2-3, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_FEDERATION_PLANET_SIGNAL_c2_choice">It could be a trap. Let's move on. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_FEDERATION_PLANET_SIGNAL_LIST_1_text">You find a secret Federation outpost. They are regrettably out of supplies but are eager to tell you of another secret base. They give you the coordinates. [ Hidden Federation Base Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_FEDERATION_PLANET_SIGNAL_LIST_2_text">You find a hidden Federation outpost. They message you, "Quick, we just got word from a sister outpost that they've been discovered by the Rebels and are under attack! If you are still loyal to the Federation, go save them!" [ Hidden Federation Base Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_FEDERATION_PLANET_SIGNAL_LIST_5_text">As you approach the signal you receive a message on a Rebel channel, "I knew we'd catch some Federation fish with this signal. Prepare to be boarded, scum!" [ Rbl SF DR, 2-3 Human Boarders; S: 0.5, 2-3, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_FRIENDLY_BEACON_c1_choice">Give them the fuel. [ x2 HScrap | Map | Weap | Reactor+1 ]</text>
<text name="event_FRIENDLY_BEACON_c2_choice">Apologize, wish them luck, and continue on. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_HIDDEN_FEDERATION_BASE_LIST_4_c1_choice">Leave. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_HIDDEN_FEDERATION_BASE_LIST_4_c2_choice">(Improved Sensors) Run a second scan pass. [ MStd ]</text>
<text name="event_HIDDEN_FEDERATION_BASE_LIST_4_c3_choice">(Advanced Sensors) Run a second scan pass. [ MScrapWeapon ]</text>
<text name="event_HIDDEN_FEDERATION_BASE_LIST_4_c4_choice">(Long-Ranged Scanners) Run a second scan pass. [ MScrapWeapon ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCENARY_c1_choice">Hire the mercenary to delay the Rebels. [ Fleet-- ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCENARY_c2_choice">Hire the mercenary to scout the sector. [ Map ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCENARY_c3_choice">Fight the ship. [ Prt SF DR; Esc: 0.5, 2-4; S: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCENARY_c4_choice">You have no need of his services. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCENARY_WORK_LIST_1_c1_choice">Agree to rescue the store. [ Space Dock Rescue Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCENARY_WORK_LIST_1_c2_choice">Decline. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCENARY_WORK_LIST_2_c1_choice">Accept. [ Prt SF S: MScrapWeapon, K: LStd, CK: LStd ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCENARY_WORK_START_c1_choice">Listen to their offer. [ More ... ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCENARY_WORK_START_c2_choice">Decline. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_DELIVER_LIST_1_c1_choice">Dock with the station and investigate. [ MDrones | Crew+, Boarders | Crew- (CB-), avoid w/Lvl 2+ Medbay ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_DELIVER_LIST_1_c2_choice">Leave it alone. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_DELIVER_LIST_1_c3_choice">(Anti-Personnel Drone) Use an Anti-Personnel Drone to investigate. [ x2 -1 Drone | -1 Drone, MStd ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_DELIVER_LIST_2_c1_choice">Accept the paltry payment.</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_DELIVER_LIST_2_c2_choice">Refuse and keep the drone parts. [ Nil | 40-55 Scrap offer ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_DELIVER_LIST_2_c3_c1_choice">Accept the new offer.</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_DELIVER_LIST_2_c3_c2_choice">Leave. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_DELIVER_LIST_2_c3_choice">(Mind Control) Convince him that he's being 'unfair'. [ 40-55 Scrap offer ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_DELIVER_LIST_2_c4_choice">(Weapons) Remain silent but power up your weapons. [ +55-70 Scrap, +2 Fuel, -5 Drones ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_INVESTIGATE_LIST_1_c1_choice">Take the cargo and head to its original destination in search of a reward. [ MDrone Reward Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_INVESTIGATE_LIST_1_c2_choice">Take the cargo for yourself. [ Weapon | HStd | MDrone Reward Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_INVESTIGATE_LIST_2_c1_choice">Promise to deliver the cargo and ask if any would be interested in joining your crew. [ Crew+, MDrone Reward Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_INVESTIGATE_LIST_2_c2_choice">Take the cargo but drop them off at a nearby station. [ Weapon | HStd | MDrone Reward Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_INVESTIGATE_LIST_2_c3_choice">(Teleporter) Beam the cargo aboard and leave them to their fate. [ Weapon | HStd | MDrone Reward Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_REQUEST_c1_choice">Yes. [ More ... ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_REQUEST_c2_choice">No. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_REQUEST_LIST_1_c1_text">"Great! I uploaded their location to your star map. I'm running out of options, so I have no choice but to trust you'll do what you have agreed to do." [ +5 Drones, Merchant Delivery Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_MERCHANT_REQUEST_LIST_2_c1_text">"At least you're confident, for what little that's worth. Here is their last known location." [ Merchant Investigate Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_CIVILIAN_BEACON_c1_choice">Aid the civilian ship. [ Prt SF K: MStd; CK: HStd; DB: [ Crew+ | MStd | LStd | LWeap | +5 Hull ] ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_CIVILIAN_BEACON_c2_choice">Stay out of it. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_CIVILIAN_BEACON_c3_choice">(Improved Weapons) Fire a warning shot from your strongest weapon. [ Straight to Double | Same as 'Aid the civilian ship' ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_STATION_CROPS_c1_choice">Attack the pirate. [ Prt SF K: MStd; S: 0.5, 2-4, MStuff; Esc: 0.5, 3-4; CK: MStd; DB: LStuff, S: MStuff ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_STATION_CROPS_c2_choice">Ignore them. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_STATION_CROPS_c3_choice">(Fire Beam) Show the pirate how to intimidate settlers: burn their crops! [ HScrapDrone ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_STATION_CROPS_c4_choice">(Fire Bomb) Show the pirate how to intimidate settlers: start fires in their crude dwellings. [ HScrapDrone, -1 Miss ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_CREWDEAD_CONTINUE_c1_choice">Agree to capture the ship. [ CrewKill Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_CREWDEAD_CONTINUE_c2_choice">Decline. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_CREWDEAD_START_2_c1_choice">Offer your services. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_CREWDEAD_START_2_c2_choice">Leave them alone. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_CREWDEAD_START_2_c3_choice">(Teleporter) Offer to board their ship. [ CrewKill Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_CREWDEAD_START_2_c4_choice">(Bio Beam) Offer to 'remove' their crew. [ CrewKill Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_CREWDEAD_START_2_c5_choice">(Fire Bomb) Offer to burn the crew out. [ CrewKill Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_CREWDEAD_text">You find the ship that you were asked to capture intact. You're not sure why, but they stressed that it's of great importance that you kill the crew WITHOUT destroying the ship. [ Prt SF K: -15 Hull; CK: HScrapWeapon ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_ESCORT_c1_choice">Accept. Accept. [ LFuel, Escore Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_ESCORT_c2_choice">Decline. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_ESCORT_ARRIVE_1_text">You escort the ship to the requested beacon. Much to your dismay you are ambushed by a Rebel ship. You walked right into their trap! [ Rbl SF DR, S: 0.5, 2-3, RStuff;Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_MANTIS_INVASION_c1_choice">Leave before they notice you. [ Nil | Mts SF K: MStd, CK: HStd ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_MANTIS_INVASION_c2_choice">(Missile Weapon) Bombard their key structures. [ -1 Miss, Mts SF K: MStd, CK: HStd ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_MANTIS_INVASION_c3_choice">(2 Fire Bombs) Teleport fire bombs into key structures. [ -2 Miss, HStuff, EngiCrew+ ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_MANTIS_INVASION_START_c1_choice">Pledge to do what you can. [ MScrap, Mantis War Camp Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_MANTIS_INVASION_START_c2_choice">Apologize and decline. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_STORE_RESCUE_c1_choice">Engage the Rebel and rescue the space dock. [ Rbl SF K: MScrap, CK: MScrap, DB: [ +5 Hull, Store ] ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_STORE_RESCUE_c2_choice">Avoid a fight. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_REBEL_VS_FEDERATION_c1_choice">Aid the Federation ship. [ Rbl SF K: MStd; CK: MStd; DB: [ Hidden Federation Base Quest | MStd | Crew+ w/BOs ]</text>
<text name="event_REBEL_VS_FEDERATION_c2_choice">Use this chance to escape. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_REBEL_VS_FEDERATION_SAVED_LIST_2_c1_choice">Quickly try to rescue the crew. [ Crew+, LStd ]</text>
<text name="event_REBEL_VS_FEDERATION_SAVED_LIST_2_c2_choice">(Nano Med-bot Dispersal) Pump their ship with Nano Med-bots to aid in the rescue. [ Crew+ w/Shield skill, HScrapFuel ]</text>
<text name="event_REBEL_VS_FEDERATION_SAVED_LIST_2_c3_choice">(Teleporter) Lock on to all remaining life signatures and beam them onto your ship. [ Crew+ w/Combat skill, MScrap, Hidden Federation Base Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_REBEL_VS_FEDERATION_SAVED_LIST_2_c4_choice">(Healing Burst) Use a healing bomb to keep them alive. [ -1 Miss, Crew+ w/Engines skill, MScrap, Hidden Federation Base Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_CRYSTAL_BEACON_c1_choice">Scrap it. [ HScrap | Rck SF DR S: 0.7, 3-4, RStuff ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_CRYSTAL_BEACON_c2_choice">Leave it alone. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_CRYSTAL_BEACON_c3_choice">(Crystal Crew) Reactivate it. [ Jump to Crystal Sector ]</text>
<text name="event_START_BEACON_text">Welcome to a new sector! Get to the exit beacon and jump to the next sector before the pursuing Rebels catch you! [ 2-3 Stores, 2-3 Items, 2-4 Neutral, 1-2 Empty, 1-2 Distress, 6-8 Hostile, 0-8 Nebula, 0-2 Quests ]</text>
<text name="event_START_GAME_text">The data you carry is vital to the remaining Federation fleet. You'll need supplies for the journey, so make sure to explore each sector before moving on to the next. But get to the exit before the pursuing Rebel fleet can catch up! [ 1-2 Stores, 1 Item, 2-4 Neutral, 1-2 Empty, 1-2 Distress, 6-8 Hostile, 0-4 Nebula, 1 Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_STATION_SICK_c1_choice">Dock with the station and investigate. [ MDrones | Crew+, 3-4 Human Boarders | Crew- (CB-), avoid w/Lvl 2+ Medbay ]</text>
<text name="event_STATION_SICK_c2_choice">Leave it alone. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_STATION_SICK_c3_choice">(Anti-Personnel Drone) Use an Anti-Personnel Drone to investigate. [ x2 -1 Drone | -1 Drone, MStd ]</text>
<text name="event_STATION_SICK_c4_choice">(Life Scanner) Run advanced life scans. [ Nothing | MStd ]</text>
<text name="event_STORE_RESCUE_c1_choice">See if you can assist them. [ Space Dock Rescue Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_STORE_RESCUE_c2_choice">Ignore their pleas. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_STRANDED_1_c1_choice">Invite him to join your crew. [ Crew+ ]</text>
<text name="event_STRANDED_1_c2_choice">Take him home to his family on a nearby planet in this system. [ HScrap | MScrap | +10 Hull ]</text>
<text name="event_STRANDED_2_c1_choice">Bring him back to your ship in hopes of finding some help for him. [ Crew- (CB+) | Crew+ | -5 Hull | Crew+ w/Lvl2 CB/MB) ]</text>
<text name="event_STRANDED_2_c2_choice">Leave the madman to his ravings, he's not worth the risk. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_STRANDED_2_c3_choice">(Improved Medbay) Bring him to your medbay. [ Crew+ ]</text>
<text name="event_STRANDED_2_c4_choice">(Advanced Medbay) Bring him to your medbay. [ Crew+ w/Max Skills ]</text>
<text name="event_STRANDED_2_c5_choice">(Slug Crew) "Sir, allow me to assess his mental state." [ HumanCrew+ | Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_STRANDED_BEACON_c1_choice">Go down to the surface to investigate. [ More... ]</text>
<text name="event_STRANDED_BEACON_c2_choice">Ignore the signal. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_CREW_STUDY_c1_choice">Participate in their study. [ x2 LScrap | 2 Boarders, Prt SF K: MStd, CK: HStd, DB: LStuff ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_CREW_STUDY_c2_choice">Decline. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_CREW_STUDY_c3_choice">(Advanced Medbay) Give them your medical records. [ Drone, LStuff ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_CREW_STUDY_c4_choice">(Damaged Stasis Pod) Ask if they can fix this. [ CrystalCrew+ ]</text>
<text name="ship_DONOR_MANTIS_CHASE1_escape_text">You pick up more chatter from the enemy ship, "You know what... Forget this. Prepare for retreat!" Looks like they're preparing to make a hasty get away! [ K: MStd, CK: HStd, Esc: Mantis Chase Quest ]</text>
<text name="ship_DONOR_MANTIS_CHASE1_gotaway_c1_choice">After them! [ Mantis Quest Chase ]</text>
<text name="ship_DONOR_MANTIS_CHASE1_gotaway_c2_choice">Forget it. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="ship_DONOR_MANTIS_CHASE2_escape_text">They appear to be trying to get away again. You doubt they'll forget to mask their jump signature this time. [ K: MStd Weapon; CK: HStd Weapon; S: 2-2, HWeap; Esc: 6-6, 12s, HStd ]</text>
<text name="ship_DONOR_MANTIS_CHASE2_surrender_c1_choice">Let them live. [ HWeap ]</text>
<text name="ship_DONOR_MANTIS_CHASE2_surrender_c2_choice">Finish them off. [ K: MStd Weapon; CK: HStd Weapon; Esc: 6-6, 12s, HStd ]</text>
<text name="text_TRAP_BEACON_TEXT_1">You arrive at the beacon and immediately detect a pirate ship. It seems this distress beacon was a trap! [ Prt SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_TRAP_BEACON_TEXT_2">"Haha! I knew someone would fall into our dastardly trap!" It appears this distress beacon was nothing but a decoy for a pirate ambush. [ Prt SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_TRAP_BEACON_TEXT_3">Your cockpit lights up with warning signals. You are being targeted by a nearby ship. The distress call was a lure to attract unwitting ships into weapons range. You prepare for a fight. [ Prt SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_TRAP_BEACON_TEXT_4">As soon as you arrive at the distress signal, shots are fired toward your ship. A trap! [ Prt SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>

<!-- data/events_boss.xml -->
<text name="event_LAST_STAND_START_c1_c1_text">Tully responds, "It's settled. The Rebels will be here in a matter of moments. We will do what we can to hold off their warships but you must succeed in destroying this flagship. Your current outpost can provide some repairs and fuel, and the other repair stations can provide aid as well. Good luck." [ 1 Store, 3 Repair, 6 Hostile, 7-10 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_FLEETS_BOTH_FIGHT_1">You arrive in the middle of a raging battle. Both sides are taking heavy losses. A small squadron flies past and a fighter breaks off, moving toward your position. [ Rbl SF K: LScrap, CK: MStd ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_FLEETS_BOTH_FIGHT_2">Two fleets fight nearby. You try to skirt around the edges of the battle and keep out of weapons range, but a Rebel scout spots you and moves in. [ Rbl SF K: LScrap, CK: MStd ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_FLEETS_BOTH_FIGHT_3">It's hard to tell who is winning the nearby battle. Before you have a chance to figure it out, a fighter moves in to attack. [ Rbl SF K: LScrap, CK: MStd ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_FLEETS_BOTH_FIGHT_4">The sheer scale of the destruction in the distance is almost breath-taking. Unfortunately, your position as an independent observer doesn't last for long! [ Rbl SF K: LScrap, CK: MStd ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_FLEETS_BOTH_FIGHT_5">The destruction in the distance is almost awe-inspiring. However you're dragged back to reality as Sensors indicate you are under attack. [ Rbl SF K: LScrap, CK: MStd ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_FLEETS_BOTH_FIGHT_6">You don't have any time to worry about the battle in the distance. The fight is coming to you really quickly! [ Rbl SF K: LScrap, CK: MStd ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_FLEETS_REBEL_1">Although you were expecting the Rebels, you never imagined their fleet could have grown so fast. You scanners can hardly register them all before a fighter stationed nearby moves in to attack. [ Rbl SF K: LScrap, CK: MStd ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_FLEETS_REBEL_2">This system is flooded with Rebel warships. Luckily your ship's signature is disguised as a civilian transport. Most heavy vessels ignore you but a small fighter is approaching with weapons hot! [ Rbl SF K: LScrap, CK: MStd ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_FLEETS_REBEL_3">You arrive to find a Rebel battalion encircling a nearby planet, launching landing parties. A small scout moves toward your position. Prepare for a fight! [ Rbl SF K: LScrap, CK: MStd ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_FLEETS_REBEL_4">As soon as you arrive you find yourself in the debris of a fierce battle. However, only Rebel warships remain and you find yourself immediately under attack. [ Rbl SF K: LScrap, CK: MStd ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_FLEETS_REBEL_5">Shots fly by and your computer registers multiple weapon locks as soon as you arrive. Evasive action! [ Rbl SF K: LScrap, CK: MStd ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_FLEETS_REBEL_6">What was once a great series of space stations is now nothing but a small ring of debris around the nearby moon. There's no time to mourn the dead; an enemy approaches! [ Rbl SF K: LScrap, CK: MStd ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_FLEETS_REBEL_7">The Federation seems to have put up a good fight. A number of Rebel ships lie broken or wounded. However their overwhelming numbers force the remaining Federation forces to retreat. Hopefully you can get away in time as well. [ Rbl SF K: LScrap, CK: MStd ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_SCOUT_1">Although this sector is still under Federation control, a small scout has slipped by the fleet. You move in to engage. [ Rbl/Auto SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_SCOUT_2">Long range scanners show this system is empty of any capital ships. Clearly it is not of strategic value. Wait... FTL signatures show a Rebel scout just jumped nearby! [ Rbl/Auto SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_SCOUT_3">Sensors indicate that the Rebels are setting up a forward Jump Beacon behind the nearby planet's moon. More importantly, a number of ships are passing by; prepare for a fight! [ Rbl/Auto SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_SCOUT_4">Federation ships are scarce in this region of space despite a number of civilian space stations. You see a small bomber squadron engaged with some Federation scouts and quickly move in to assist. [ Rbl/Auto SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_SCOUT_5">As soon as you arrive at the beacon, a Rebel scout turns to engage. Power up the weapons! [ Rbl/Auto SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_SCOUT_6">You scan the area, finding signatures for only a small trade vessel. However, as it approaches you see the silhouette of a Rebel scout! You run the scanners again and discover their registration is fake. You move in to attack. [ Rbl/Auto SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_SCOUT_RESCUE_1">Shots fly by your port windows followed by a Rebel scout in pursuit of a damaged cruiser. Should we move in to engage? [ Rbl SF K: MStd, Esc: 0.5, 4-8, CK: HStd, DB: [ Sincere Gratitude | +8 Hull | MStuff | Repair Station Quest ] ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_SCOUT_RESCUE_2">There seems to be a small Federation colony under attack by a Rebel forward scout. Will you protect them? [ Rbl SF K: MStd, Esc: 0.5, 4-8, CK: HStd, DB: [ Sincere Gratitude | +8 Hull | MStuff | Repair Station Quest ] ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_SCOUT_RESCUE_3">A number of large transports are being pursued by a Rebel bombing squadron. One bomber has managed to slip through the defensive fire, and is poised to wreak havoc among the enormous yet vulnerable transports. There's time for you to advance and take it out! [ Rbl SF K: MStd, Esc: 0.5, 4-8, CK: HStd, DB: [ Sincere Gratitude | +8 Hull | MStuff | Repair Station Quest ] ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_SCOUT_RESCUE_4">A battle rages nearby between small fighters; apparently fighting over a space station. The Federation appears to be losing ships fast. Shall we assist them? [ Rbl SF K: MStd, Esc: 0.5, 4-8, CK: HStd, DB: [ Sincere Gratitude | +8 Hull | MStuff | Repair Station Quest ] ]</text>
<text name="text_BOSS_SCOUT_RESCUE_5">A civilian ship is broadcasting a request for assistance on a secure Federation channel. They are being harassed by Rebel scouts. Will you respond? [ Rbl SF K: MStd, Esc: 0.5, 4-8, CK: HStd, DB: [ Sincere Gratitude | +8 Hull | MStuff | Repair Station Quest ] ]</text>

<!-- data/events_crystal.xml -->
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_AUTO_text">The Rebels must have sent their automated scouts to find you. One jumps in and immediately moves to attack. [ Auto SF DR ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_CACHE_c1_choice">Attempt to break through with the weapons you have. [ x2 Nil | [ LStuff, Crystal Weapon | LStuff, Crystal Weapon, 2-3 Crystal Boarders | [ Crew- (CB+) or [ -100 Fuel, Weapon, LStuff or BOs ] ] ] ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_CACHE_c2_choice">(Breach Missiles) Use a Breach Missile. [ -1 Miss, [ LStuff, Crystal Weapon | LStuff, Crystal Weapon, 2-3 Crystal Boarders | [ Crew- (CB+) or [ -100 Fuel, Weapon, LStuff or BOs ] ] ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_CACHE_c3_choice">(Crystal crewmember) Have your Crystalline Being recalibrate your weapons. [ L Stuff, Crystal Weapon | L Stuff, Crystal Weapon, 2-3 Crystal Boarders | [ -1 Crew (CB+) or [ -100 Fuel, Weapon, L Stuff or BOs ] ] ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_CACHE_LIST_3_c1_choice">Pull out now! [ Crew- (CB+) ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_CACHE_LIST_3_c2_choice">Detonate your entire fuel reserves to escape with your crew and the cargo. [ -100 Fuel, Weapon, LStuff ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_CACHE_LIST_3_c3_choice">(Improved Teleporter) Beam your crewmember back on board. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_CACHE_LIST_3_c4_choice">(Advanced Engines) Rescue your crewmember and the cargo. [ Weapon, LStuff ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_CHATTY_c1_choice">Yes. [ More... ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_CHATTY_c1_c1_choice">Try to answer his questions. [ +6 Hull | RStuff | Rbl SF DR ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_CHATTY_c1_c2_choice">"I don't have time for this." [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_CHATTY_c2_choice">No. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_CHATTY_c3_choice">(Crystal Crew) Have your crew speak to them. [ RScrapFuel ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_CONVOY_text">A large convoy of lumbering civilian ships appears to be passing through this region. You show no hostile intentions, but they are taking no chances, immediately sending their escort to attack! [ Cry SF K: MStd, CK: MStd, S: [ LScrapFuel, +8 Hull ] ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_FED_c1_choice">Save the Federation ship. [ Cry SF K: MStd, CK: HStd, DB: [ RStuff | LStd, Crew+ ] ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_FED_c2_choice">Prepare to leave. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_FED_DESERTER_c1_choice">Offer supplies. [ -1-3 Fuel, -15-25 Scrap, Map ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_FED_DESERTER_c2_choice">Attack the traitors. [ Fed SF DR ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_FED_DESERTER_c3_choice">Leave them be. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_HELP_DIG_c1_choice">Send a crewmember to help.</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_HELP_DIG_c1_c1_choice">Leave your crewmember behind. [ Crew- (CB-), MScrapFuel (HScrapFuel if Waited) ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_HELP_DIG_c1_c2_choice">Pull your guy out. [ Cry SF DR ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_HELP_DIG_c1_c3_choice">Wait. [ Fleet+, [ Crystal Heavy 2, HAugment if wait twice ] ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_HELP_DIG_c2_choice">Refuse. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_HUMAN_TESTS_c1_choice">Allow them to run tests on a crewmember. [ Crew- (CB+) | LScrapWeapon | MStuff | LScrapDrone ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_HUMAN_TESTS_c2_choice">Refuse. [ x2 Nil | Cry SF DR ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_HUMAN_TESTS_c3_choice">(Rock crewmember) Send your Rockman crew. [ MStd ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_HUMAN_TESTS_c4_choice">(Backup DNA Bank) Send your crew's data. [ MScrapWeapon ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_HUNTER_text">Crystal shards fly past your ship as soon as you jump. You scan to find the assailant and discover a Crystalline ship carrying a number of humans in its cargo bay. It must be hunting the intruding ships! [ Cry SF K: MStd, CK: MStd, S: HumanCrew+ ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_MANTIS_CRYSTAL_c1_choice">Attack the Mantis. [ Mts SF K: MStd, CK: HStd, DB: [ x2 Nil | x2 RStuff | Crystal Weapon ] ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_MANTIS_CRYSTAL_c2_choice">Ignore them. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_PIRATE_CRYSTAL_c1_choice">Attack the pirate. [ Prt SF K: MStd, CK, HStd, DB: [ x2 Nil | x2 RStuff | Crystal Weapon ] ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_PIRATE_CRYSTAL_c2_choice">Ignore them. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_REBEL_text">As soon as you arrive, a Rebel ship jumps in after you; they must be really hot on your tail. [ Rbl SF DR ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_REBEL_CRYSTAL_c1_choice">Attack the Rebel. [ Rbl SF K: MStd, CK: HStd, DB: [ x2 Nil | x2 RStuff | Crystal Weapon ] ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_REBEL_CRYSTAL_c2_choice">Attack the Crystalline ship. [ Cry SF DR ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_REBEL_CRYSTAL_c3_choice">Ignore them. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_REBEL_CRYSTAL2_c1_choice">Engage the Rebel ship. [ Cry SF DR ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_REBEL_CRYSTAL2_c2_choice">Leave them alone. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_REQUEST_c1_c1_choice">Give them your flight plans. [ HScrap, Fleet+ ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_REQUEST_c1_c2_choice">Accept the scrap but give them false flight plans. [ HScrap, Fleet- | 1-2 Crystal Borders, Cry SF DR ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_REQUEST_c1_c3_choice">(Distraction Buoy) Accept the scrap but give them falsified flight plans. [ HScrap, Fleet- ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_REQUEST_c1_c4_choice">Refuse. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_SCRAP_EXCITED_c1_choice">Offer 35 scrap. [ CrystalCrew+ or [ Crystal Bomb | Crystal Burst 2 ] ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_SCRAP_EXCITED_c1_c1_choice">Accept. [ CrystalCrew+ ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_SCRAP_EXCITED_c1_c2_choice">Request another payment. [ Crystal Bomb | Crystal Burst 2 ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_SCRAP_EXCITED_c2_choice">Turn him down. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_SHIP_SURRENDER_7_c1_choice">Yes. [ CrystalCrew+]</text>
<text name="event_CRYSTAL_SHIP_SURRENDER_7_c2_choice">No. [ RStuff ]</text>
<text name="event_START_BEACON_CRYSTAL_c1_text">"You have done as you promised and so shall I. The coordinates of my old ship have been forwarded to your navigation system." [ 2-3 Stores, 2 Items, 2 Empty, 6-10 Hostile, 1-2 Boarders, 12 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_CRYSTAL_FIGHT_1">You arrive near a fleet of crystal ships, civilian or mercantile from the looks of them. You pause to scan one but they react immediately and send an escort to fight you off. Prepare to engage! [ Cry SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_CRYSTAL_FIGHT_2">You arrive at the Beacon and are immediately greeted by an automatic message or warning of some kind. The translator can't seem to discern its purpose but after a few short moments an alarm goes off and a hostile ship jumps in! [ Cry SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_CRYSTAL_FIGHT_3">You receive a message, "Hah. It looks like another worthless alien-filled craft. Prepare to meet your maker!" Weapon locks detected. [ Cry SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_CRYSTAL_FIGHT_4">A Crystalline ship messages you, "I've heard tales that our isolation has finally ended. As a warrior I must demand to test my skills against you!" Before you can respond they move in to attack. [ Cry SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_CRYSTAL_FIGHT_5">You arrive in a busy sector. At first no one pays any mind to your alien ship but soon you're registering a number of scan signatures. You get the feeling you're not wanted here just seconds before registering enemy weapon locks! [ Cry SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_CRYSTAL_FIGHT_6">You jump next to a node busy with traffic, but before long all nearby ships notice you and keep their distance, uncertain of your allegiance. After an awkward standoff, a military ship breaks away from the rest and charges you. [ Cry SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_CRYSTAL_FIGHT_7">A barrage of rasps and clicks is broadcast over the comm; the universal translator understands little, but the words 'aliens', 'allowed' and 'no' come through quite clearly. You'll have to prove your right to be here in combat! [ Cry SF DR ]</text>

<!-- data/events_engi.xml -->
<text name="event_DISTRESS_ENGI_REACTOR_c1_choice">Board the station. [ Nil | More... ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_ENGI_REACTOR_c2_choice">Ignore it. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_ENGI_REACTOR_c3_choice">(Improved Sensors) Run another scan. [ EngiCrew+, LScrap | LScrapDrone ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_ENGI_REACTOR_c4_choice">(Long Ranged Scanners) Run another scan. [ EngiCrew+, LScrap | LScrapDrone ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_ENGI_REACTOR_LIST1_2_c1_choice">Save the Engi! [ Crew- (CB+), LScrap, EngiCrew+ | LScrap, EngiCrew+ ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_ENGI_REACTOR_LIST1_2_c2_choice">Save the drone schematic. [ Crew- (CB+), LScrap | LScrapDrone ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_ENGI_REACTOR_LIST1_2_c3_choice">Save yourselves! [ LScrap ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_ENGI_REACTOR_SCAN_c1_choice">Save the Engi! [ EngiCrew+, LScrap ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_ENGI_REACTOR_SCAN_c2_choice">Save the Drone Schematic! [ LScrapDrone ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_ENGI_REBEL_text">The distress signal originates from a small Engi ship under attack by a rebel fighter - but when the Rebels see Federation markings they turn to attack! [ Rbl SF K: LStd, CK: MStd, DB: Random Buyables ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_ENGI_REBEL_RESULT_c1_choice">Give them 25 scrap. [ Nil | HealBomb | Drone ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_ENGI_REBEL_RESULT_c2_choice">Give them 40 scrap, 2 missiles and 2 fuel. [ MedBot Augment ]</text>
<text name="event_DISTRESS_ENGI_REBEL_RESULT_c3_choice">Give them nothing. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_FLEET_DELAY_c1_choice">Booby trap the cache. [ -2 Miss, Fleet-- ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_FLEET_DELAY_c2_choice">Secure the cache. [ MScrapDrone ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_PIRATE_FIGHT_text">There must have been rich pickings for pirates around here up until war broke out. The pirate you encounter here looks worn down, but hungry. You'll have to fight! [ Prt SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_REBEL_FIGHT_text">The rebel fighter here would seem to suggest elements of the rebel fleet are already making incursions on Engi space. You move to engage. [ Rbl SF DR; S: 0.5, 2-3, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_SEX_c1_choice">Attempt to help the ships by prying them apart. [ Eng SF with no rewards ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_SEX_c2_choice">Ignore the damaged vessels. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_SEX_c3_choice">(Engi Crew) Have your Engi crewmember hail the vessel and assess the damage. [ MStuff ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_SURRENDER_c1_choice">Explain that you're friendly. [ Nil | RStd ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_SURRENDER_c2_choice">Accept their offer of surrender. [ RStd ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_STATION_DISTRESS_c1_choice">Respond to the call and move in to assist. [ Eng w/Mantis Crew SF DR, 1-2 Boarders | Mts SF K: MStd, CK: HStd, DB: [ Nil | MFuel | EngiCrew+, LStd | [ Option of Fuel/Weapon/Drone/Engi BO ] ] ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_STATION_DISTRESS_c2_choice">Keep your distance. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_STATION_DISTRESS_LIST_1_text">You receive another message from the ship, this time with a Mantis at the comm-log. "Foolish meatsacks," he yells. Sensors indicate the ship is moving in to attack and boarders teleport from the station. [ Eng w/Mantis crew SF DR 1-2 Mantis Boarders ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_STATION_DISTRESS_LIST_2_text">You approach to find a Mantis ship assaulting a small Engi space station. You prepare for a fight! [ Mts SF K: MStd, CK: HStd, DB: [ Nil | MFuel | EngiCrew+, LStd | [ Option of Fuel/Weapon/Drone/Engi BO ] ] ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_UNLOCK_3_text">You have finally caught up with the ships you've been hunting. A hangar-sized cargo ship is being escorted by a number of Mantis ships. As you reconsider the assault, a squadron of Engi ships with pirate emblems jump in and assist you. You prepare to fight the Mantis but scans indicate they are manned by Rebels! [ Mts w/Human crew SF CK: MStd, DB: +20 Hull, HStd, Titanium System Casing ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_VIRUS_c1_c1_choice">Hold on! Let us try to purge the system code! [ Eng SF w/Shields@0 + Engines@0, K: MStd, CK: MStd ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_VIRUS_c1_c2_choice">Attack the Engi vessel! [ Eng SF K:MStd, CK: MStd ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_VIRUS_c1_c3_choice">(Hacking System) Isolate and quarantine the virus. [ LStd, Drone Reactor Booster ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_VIRUS_c1_c4_choice">(Improved Hacking) Reprogram the virus. [ +15 Hull, Reactor+1, Drone Reactor Booster ]</text>
<text name="event_ENGI_VIRUS_c1_c5_choice">(Advanced Hacking) Reprogram the virus. [ +30 Hull, Reactor+1, Drone Reactor Booster ]</text>
