<text name="event_NEBULA_WEAPONS_TRADER_LIST2_1_c1_choice">Buy the weapon. [ -45 Scrap, Weapon ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_WEAPONS_TRADER_LIST2_1_c2_choice">Decline. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_WEAPONS_TRADER_LIST2_2_text">Once "convinced" to help, he casually states that his offer was actually a lie and that they planned to attack your ship. By the time he returns to his senses you've already prepared your ship to fight. [ Prt SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_WEAPONS_TRADER_c1_choice">Ignore the ship. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_WEAPONS_TRADER_c2_choice">Attack the ship. [ Prt SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_WEAPONS_TRADER_c3_choice">Purchase an unknown weapon for 45 scrap. [ -45 Scrap, Weapon | -45 Scrap [ Prt SF DR or Nil ] ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_WEAPONS_TRADER_c4_choice">(Mind Control) Convince him to make it a better deal. [ -45 Scrap, Weapon or Nil | Prt SF DR ]</text>
<text name="event_STORM_AUTO_c1_choice">Prepare to fight. [ Auto SF DR ]</text>
<text name="event_STORM_AUTO_c2_choice">(Engines) Attempt to out-run it. [ Nil | Auto SF DR ]</text>
<text name="event_STORM_AUTO_c3_choice">(Improved Engines) Attempt to out-run it. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_STORM_AUTO_c4_choice">(Cloaking) Use your cloaking to escape. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_STORM_ITEMS_c1_choice">Manually search the wreckage for survivors and equipment. [ -4 Hull, HStuff | Crew+, LStd | Crew- (CB+), LStd | MScrapDrone | MScrapWeapon ]</text>
<text name="event_STORM_ITEMS_c2_choice">Avoid the risk and wait to jump away unscathed. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_STORM_ITEMS_c3_choice">(Piloting) Have your pilot carefully explore the debris. [ Crew+, LStd | MScrapDrone | LScrapWeapon | Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_STORM_REBEL_text">You arrive in the middle of a plasma storm. Despite the harsh conditions, a Rebel scout seems to be waiting for you. [ Rbl SF DR w/Ion-Storm; S: 0.5, 2-3, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_AUTO_LIST_1">You cross paths with an advance scout of the Rebel fleet searching this section of the nebula for your ship. [ Auto SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_AUTO_LIST_2">You jump into a calmer part of the nebula. However, your relief fades as a Rebel scout jumps to the beacon and moves in to attack. [ Auto SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_AUTO_LIST_3">The tangled wrecks of many ships wait in dormancy here. You see lights flicker on what looks like debris. A Rebel scout bursts out of the wreckage! [ Auto SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_AUTO_LIST_4">This drone isn't looking for you. Perhaps it's scouting ahead for the Rebel expansion or maybe they're seeking to use this nebula for cover. Regardless, it identifies you as hostile. [ Auto SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_AUTO_LIST_5">It's worrying that the Rebels have penetrated so deep into uncharted space, even if it is only an unmanned craft. It arms its weapons; you should do the same. [ Auto SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_MANTIS_FIGHT_1">Nebulas are known to be popular Mantis hunting grounds. Information you would have done well to heed here. [ Mts SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_MANTIS_FIGHT_2">You detect a Mantis expedition vessel returning home with its haul. So determined are they, in fact, that they don't wait to see if you're hostile before firing. [ Mts SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_MANTIS_FIGHT_3">A Mantis ship, lost in the storm, hails you. "Sensors are out. We have no local telemetry. We will take yours." You detect a power increase in their weapons systems. [ Mts SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_MANTIS_FIGHT_4">A Mantis ship hails you through the storm: "These are sacred Urggghtnag clan hunting grounds. You are prey." Shields up! [ Mts SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_MANTIS_FIGHT_5">You notice a Mantis attack ship ducking between the clouds of swirling space stuff; it's hunting you. You try to get the jump and move in to attack. [ Mts SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_PIRATE_1">As you drift through the nebula an unmarked vessel descends from the clouds and into your wake. Their weapons come online. [ Prt SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_PIRATE_2">A pirate ship pulls out of the ether and hails: "You know what I love about this part of the galaxy? The explorers! You always carry such fine loot." They lock weapons. [ Prt SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_PIRATE_3">As you coast through the nebula a pirate ship matches your course and closes the distance. Better to pick your battleground, but beggars can't be choosers. [ Prt SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_PIRATE_4">A hostile vessel descends from out of the nebula. Combat stations! [ Prt SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_PIRATE_5">You try to read the ID of a ship ahead in the fog, but it's too thick to penetrate. You have your answer when the ship turns, weapons hot! [ Prt SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_REBEL_LIST_1">You cross paths with an advance scout of the Rebel fleet searching this section of the nebula for your ship. [ Rbl SF DR; S: 0.5, 2-3, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_REBEL_LIST_2">A ship bearing Rebel colors can be seen waiting near the beacon. They must have been waiting for you, since they engage immediately. [ Rbl SF DR; S: 0.5, 2-3, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_REBEL_LIST_3">The Rebels must have anticipated you would try to lose them within the nebula. A scout is waiting for you at the beacon. [ Rbl SF DR; S: 0.5, 2-3, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_REBEL_LIST_4">It looks like you will be unable to avoid the Rebels by traveling through the nebula. A Rebel ship is waiting for you near the beacon. [ Rbl SF DR; S: 0.5, 2-3, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_REBEL_LIST_5">Shortly after you arrive, a Rebel ship jumps nearby. There looks to be no escape. Prepare for a fight! [ Rbl SF DR; S: 0.5, 2-3, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_REBEL_LIST_6">Newton-knows what brings this Rebel ship so far out; its captain hails, but does a double take when he identifies your ship. They open fire. [ Rbl SF DR; S: 0.5, 2-3, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_REBEL_LIST_7">A Rebel ship hails, but you don't take chances in conditions like this. You block the frequency and prepare to engage. [ Rbl SF DR; S: 0.5, 2-3, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_NEBULA_1">This nebula must have been an important hub at one point; placing all of these jump beacons would be no easy task. However, now it's hardly navigable. [ 0-1 Non-Nebula Store, 1-3 Items, 1 Nebula Store, 4 Empty Nebula, 5-6 Hostile, 7-8 Neutral, 1-3 Distress ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_NEBULA_2">Nebulas were always dangerous places. Many electronics fail in these clouds. You will have to tread lightly. [ 0-1 Non-Nebula Store, 1-3 Items, 1 Nebula Store, 4 Empty Nebula, 5-6 Hostile, 7-8 Neutral, 1-3 Distress ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_NEBULA_3">You've entered a sector thick with nebulas. You'll have to navigate on instinct. [ 0-1 Non-Nebula Store, 1-3 Items, 1 Nebula Store, 4 Empty Nebula, 5-6 Hostile, 7-8 Neutral, 1-3 Distress ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_NEBULA_4">You've entered a nebula-rich sector. You may put a few light years on the fleet, but that's only useful if you make it out the other side. [ 0-1 Non-Nebula Store, 1-3 Items, 1 Nebula Store, 4 Empty Nebula, 5-6 Hostile, 7-8 Neutral, 1-3 Distress ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_NEBULA_5">Thanks to the high nebula density of this sector very little of it has been charted, and rumours of what lurks in the depths abound. [ 0-1 Non-Nebula Store, 1-3 Items, 1 Nebula Store, 4 Empty Nebula, 5-6 Hostile, 7-8 Neutral, 1-3 Distress ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_NEBULA_6">The gases that make up the nebulas in this sector threaten to impair your systems; but you have to press on. [ 0-1 Non-Nebula Store, 1-3 Items, 1 Nebula Store, 4 Empty Nebula, 5-6 Hostile, 7-8 Neutral, 1-3 Distress ]</text>

<!-- data/events_pirate.xml -->
<text name="event_FLOATING_CARGO_c1_choice">Bring it aboard. [ MStd | LScrap | 2-4 Human Boarders | 2-4 Human Boarders, Prt SF DR; S: 0-5, RStuff; Esc: 0.3, 2-4, 15s ]</text>
<text name="event_FLOATING_CARGO_c2_choice">Leave it alone, this looks suspicious. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_FLOATING_CARGO_c3_choice">(Advanced Sensors) Run an advanced scan on the boxes. [ 20-35 Scrap | MStd | [ Prt SF DR; S: 0-5, RStuff; Esc: 0.3, 2-4, 15s or Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_FLOATING_CARGO_c4_choice">(Long-Ranged Scanners) Run an advanced scan on the boxes. [ 20-35 Scrap | MStd | Prt SF DR; S: 0-5, RStuff; Esc: 0.3, 2-4, 15s Prt SF DR or Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_FLOATING_CARGO_SCAN_LIST_3_c1_choice">Destroy the crates to prevent another ship from falling victim. [ Prt SF DR; S: 0-5, RStuff; Esc: 0.3, 2-4, 15s ]</text>
<text name="event_FLOATING_CARGO_SCAN_LIST_3_c2_choice">Leave it alone and prepare to jump. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_FRIENDLY_SLAVER_c1_choice">Buy one slave and free them to join your crew. [ Crew+, -25-45 Scrap ]</text>
<text name="event_FRIENDLY_SLAVER_c2_choice">Attack the slaver scum. [ Prt SF; S: 0.2, 2-4, Crew+; Esc: 0.5, 2-4; K: HStd; CK: [ Rock/Mantis/Engi, MStd | Crew+, HStd | Hstd ] ]</text>
<text name="event_FRIENDLY_SLAVER_c3_choice">Ignore the slaver and continue on your way. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_FRIENDLY_SLAVER_c4_choice">(Teleporter) Use your teleporter to attempt to board the ship and release some of the slaves. [ x2 Crew+, same as above | Same as above ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_ASTEROID_c1_choice">Turn and fight. [ Prt SF DR w/asteroids; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_BRIBER_c1_choice">Accept their bribe. [ LStd ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_BRIBER_c2_choice">Try to be a hero. Attack the pirate. [ Prt SF; S: 0.2, 3-4, HStuff; Esc: 0.4, 3-4, Double; K: RScrap; CK: MStd, DB: [ [ LStd or Fleet- ] | MScrap | Nil | Store | +15 Hull ] ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_BRIBER_WIN_1_c1_choice">Destroy the ship and salvage it. [ LStd ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_BRIBER_WIN_1_c2_choice">Use the leverage you gained by saving their lives to convince them to delay the pursuing fleet. [ Fleet- ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_CHOICE_c1_choice">Pay their toll [ -15-25 Scrap ].</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_CHOICE_c2_choice">Reject their 'offer'. [ Prt SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_CIVILIAN_c1_choice">Aid the civilian ship. [ Prt SF K: MStd, CK: HStd, DB: [ Crew+ | MStd | LStd | LScrapWeapon | +5 Hull ] ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_CIVILIAN_c2_choice">Stay out of it. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_NO_ESCAPE_c2_choice">(Hacking System) Counter the remote hacking. [ Prt SF Hacking@0, K: RScrapFuel, CK: MScrapFuel ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_NO_ESCAPE_text">Once you arrive, your screen lights up with warnings. A nearby pirate seems to have advanced hacking tools and they have tried to shut down your engines. Your crew manages to keep them barely operational and you move into attack. [ Prt SF Engines@1, K: RScrapFuel, CK: MSCrapFuel ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_SLAVER_c1_choice">Draw straws and send a crew-member over to the slavers. [ Crew- (CB-) ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_SLAVER_c2_choice">We will never surrender one of our crew to slavers! [ Prt SF; S: 0.2, 2-4, Crew+; Esc: 0.5, 2-4; K: HStd; CK: [ Rock/Mantis/Engi, MStd | Crew+, HStd | HStd ] ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_SLAVER_c3_choice">(Engines) Attempt to out-run the slaver ship. [ x2 Nil | Same as above ]</text>
<text name="event_PIRATE_SUN_text">This beacon has been placed too close to a super-giant class M star! The ship will gradually overheat until you get out of here... or die. A pirate, apparently oblivious to the danger of the sun, moves in to engage. [ Prt SF DR; S; 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_SAVE_CIVILIAN_LIST_1_c1_choice">Welcome aboard! [ Crew+ ]</text>
<text name="event_SAVE_CIVILIAN_LIST_1_c2_choice">Decline their request. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_SAVE_CIVILIAN_LIST_4_c1_choice">The captain offers to install a piece of equipment on your ship. [ LScrapWeapon ]</text>
<text name="text_PIRATE_1">As you jump into the system a pirate advances on your position. They are refusing all hails. Prepare for a fight. [ Prt SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_PIRATE_2">Soon after arriving in the system you are hailed by a small cruiser. "What good fortune that we happen to run into each other. Nothing personal, but you have some information we need!" [ Prt SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_PIRATE_3">At first it appears you've arrived in an empty system, but a ship appears from behind a planet and hails you: "Haha! I am the dread pirate Tuco, prepare to die!" [ Prt SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_PIRATE_4">The only other ship at this beacon messages you: "Finally, after months of waiting, someone has fallen into our trap!" [ Prt SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_PIRATE_5">You barely have time to register jump completion before your ship warns you of an incoming ship with weapons hot. [ Prt SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_PIRATE_1">A few years ago this region was bustling with trade activity. Now it is overrun with bandits and marauders. You should tread lightly here. [ 1-2 Stores, 1-2 Items, 1 Boarders, 1-2 Distress, 0-5 Nebula, 1-2 Empty, 6-8 Hostile, 0-1 Quest, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_PIRATE_2">This somewhat isolated region was thrown into chaos at the start of the rebellion. Even in peacetime it was always beset by pirates but now it houses a center of operations for countless pirate fleets. [ 1-2 Stores, 1-2 Items, 1 Boarders, 1-2 Distress, 0-5 Nebula, 1-2 Empty, 6-8 Hostile, 0-1 Quest, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_PIRATE_3">If the reports are true, this area has been under the control of pirates for quite some time. Some traders still attempt to trade with the few settlements that remain, but they do so at great risk. [ 1-2 Stores, 1-2 Items, 1 Boarders, 1-2 Distress, 0-5 Nebula, 1-2 Empty, 6-8 Hostile, 0-1 Quest, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_PIRATE_4">A few Federation-friendly planets still exist in this sector, but they are constantly under attack by pirate raids. This is a dangerous sector, so be careful. [ 1-2 Stores, 1-2 Items, 1 Boarders, 1-2 Distress, 0-5 Nebula, 1-2 Empty, 6-8 Hostile, 0-1 Quest, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>

<!-- data/events_rebel.xml -->
<text name="event_AUTO_CIVILIAN_c1_choice">Aid the civilian ship. [ Auto SF K: LStd, CK: MStd, DB: [ Crew+ | MStd | LStd | LScrapWeapon | +5 Hull ] ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_CIVILIAN_c2_choice">Stay out of it. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_DEFENSE_ITEM_c1_choice">Attack the automated ship to get to the storage cache. [ Auto SF K: MScrap, DB: [ LScrapDrone | Nil | LScrapWeapon | MStuff ] ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_DEFENSE_ITEM_c2_choice">Avoid provoking the ship. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_DEFENSE_ITEM_c3_choice">(Cloaking) Attempt to cloak and access the cache. [ Auto SF K: MScrap, DB: [ LScrapDrone | Nil | LScrapWeapon | MStuff ] | [ LScrapDrone | Nil | LScrapWeapon | MStuff ] ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_DEFENSE_MAP_c1_choice">Attack the automated ship to get to the sensor station. [ Auto SF K: LScrap, DB: Map ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_DEFENSE_MAP_c2_choice">Avoid provoking the ship. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_DEFENSE_MAP_c3_choice">(Sensors) Use your sensors to attempt to access the data. [ Map | Auto SF K: LScrap, DB: Map ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_DEFENSE_MAP_c4_choice">(Teleporter) Beam directly onto the station to try to avoid detection. [ Map ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_DEFENSE_RADAR_c1_choice">Approach the station. [ Auto SF K: MScrap, More... ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_DEFENSE_RADAR_c2_choice">Keep your distance and wait for the FTL to charge. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_DEFENSE_RADAR_c3_choice">(Combat Drone) Send a drone to distract the automated ship. [ Drones -1 [ x2 [ Fleet- | Map | Nil | Fleet+ ] | Same as above ] ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_HACKER_c2_choice">(Hacking System) Counter the remote hacking. [ Slg SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_HACKER_text">Your arrival is greeted by numerous computer alerts. The nearby automated Rebel scout has used a local satellite to deploy a virus to disrupt your Shields System. Hopefully it won't cause further problems before you can destroy it. [ Auto SF Shields@Half, K: MStd ]</text>
<text name="event_BROKEN_REBEL_DRONE_c1_choice">Attempt to download the ship's data stores. [ Map, LStd | Auto SF DR ]</text>
<text name="event_BROKEN_REBEL_DRONE_c2_choice">Don't risk activating it, and just strip the ship for any useful scrap. [ LScrap ]</text>
<text name="event_BROKEN_REBEL_DRONE_c3_choice">(Sensors) Remotely scan the ship. [ LStd | More... ]</text>
<text name="event_BROKEN_REBEL_DRONE_SENSORS_2_c1_choice">Yes. [ Map, LStd | Auto SF DR ]</text>
<text name="event_BROKEN_REBEL_DRONE_SENSORS_2_c2_choice">No. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_FLAGSHIP_CONSTRUCTION_c1_choice">Look around. [ MiniFlagship SF K: 5 Fuel, 5 Missiles, 5 Drones, HScrapWeapon, Fleet-- ]</text>
<text name="event_FLAGSHIP_CONSTRUCTION_c2_choice">Leave immediately. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_REBEL_TRANSPORT_c1_choice">Demand the surrender of their goods. [ Rbl SF Esc: 14-14, 40s; K: [ MScrapWeapon | LStd | LScrapWeapon | MScrap | MScrapDrone | MScrapDrones | x2 M ScrapOnly | x2 LStd | HStd ]; CK: [ MScrapWeapon | Crew+, HScrap | MScrap | MScrapDrone ] ]</text>
<text name="event_REBEL_TRANSPORT_c2_choice">Avoid the ship. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_REFUEL_STATION_c1_choice">Intervene to defend the outpost. [ Auto SF K: LStd, DB: MStd ]</text>
<text name="event_AUTO_REFUEL_STATION_c2_choice">Avoid the conflict. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_SQUAT_REFUEL_STATION_c1_choice">Intervene to defend the outpost. [ Rbl SF K: MStd, CK: HStd, DB: MScrapFuel ]</text>
<text name="event_SQUAT_REFUEL_STATION_c2_choice">Avoid the conflict. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="text_BOARDERS_REBEL_SHIP_1">You receive a message from a nearby Rebel station, "You have a lot of guts passing through our space, I'll give you that." He turns giving an order, "Kill their crew, I want that ship intact." [ Rbl SF DR; 2-3 Human Boarders; S: 0.5, 2-3, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_BOARDERS_REBEL_SHIP_2">Your sensors warn of an incoming Rebel ship at the same time as you hear the telltale signs of a teleporter. You hear someone taunt from within the ship, "Ready to die? I sure am ready to get a promotion!" [ Rbl SF DR; 2-3 Human Boarders; S: 0.5, 2-3, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_BOARDERS_REBEL_SHIP_3">Incoming message, "Hello Captain," says a Rebel in an officer's garb. "How very generous of you to turn yourself in. Prepare to be boarded. Come quietly and we may be lenient." [ Rbl SF DR; 2-3 Human Boarders; S: 0.5, 2-3, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_BOARDERS_REBEL_SHIP_4">You receive a message on a low-band channel. "You're surrounded, just like the last of your Federation friends. Just die already." The enemy has teleported onto your ship! [ Rbl SF DR; 2-3 Human Boarders; S: 0.5, 2-3, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_1">Your ship is hailed. "We've found you at last. Prepare to die!" [ Rbl SF DR, S: [ 0.5, 2-3, RStuff ], Esc: [ 0.5, 3-4 ] ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_10">A Rebel ship is guarding this beacon. You order a pursuit course and prepare to scratch up one more. [ Rbl SF DR, S: [ 0.5, 2-3, RStuff ], Esc: [ 0.5, 3-4 ] ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_2">A small Rebel ship is docked at a small station. You try to lay low but it spots you. Power up the weapons! [ Rbl SF DR, S: [ 0.5, 2-3, RStuff ], Esc: [ 0.5, 3-4 ] ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_3">A Rebel ship has been patrolling this region. As soon as you arrive it begins its assault. [ Rbl SF DR, S: [ 0.5, 2-3, RStuff ], Esc: [ 0.5, 3-4 ] ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_4">A Rebel ship hails you: "Federation scum! We've waited a long time for this!" [ Rbl SF DR, S: [ 0.5, 2-3, RStuff ], Esc: [ 0.5, 3-4 ] ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_5">You receive a transmission: "Sorry sir, this is nothing personal but we're under orders." The Rebel ship's weapons go hot. [ Rbl SF DR, S: [ 0.5, 2-3, RStuff ], Esc: [ 0.5, 3-4 ] ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_6">By the time you notice the Rebel ship behind the beacon, it's too late to avoid a fight. [ Rbl SF DR, S: [ 0.5, 2-3, RStuff ], Esc: [ 0.5, 3-4 ] ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_7">A Rebel ship hails. "We did not fight a war to let a single Federation ship shatter our dreams of a better galaxy!" He locks weapons. [ Rbl SF DR, S: [ 0.5, 2-3, RStuff ], Esc: [ 0.5, 3-4 ] ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_8">A Rebel ship approaches cautiously. "Personally," says the captain, "I'd have stuck with the Federation. But I'm a soldier, sir, and I'm no use without a war to fight. Raise your shields!" [ Rbl SF DR, S: [ 0.5, 2-3, RStuff ], Esc: [ 0.5, 3-4 ] ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_9">You're hailed by a Rebel ship: "When the rebellion is complete you'll see the safer world we provide. Well, you won't, but you get the point." They arm weapons. [ Rbl SF DR, S: [ 0.5, 2-3, RStuff ], Esc: [ 0.5, 3-4 ] ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_AUTO_1">You discover one of the Rebel's autonomous scouts. The ship's AI wastes no time in engaging your ship. [ Auto SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_AUTO_2">Your ship is hailed: "This is an automated message. Resisting our takeover is pointless. Prepare to die." It appears this Rebel ship is run by an AI. [ Auto SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_AUTO_3">A Rebel autonomous scout is exploring this beacon. You attempt to hide behind a nearby moon, but the ship finds you and begins its assault. [ Auto SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_AUTO_4">The AI of a nearby small Rebel scout immediately identifies you as a threat and engages. [ Auto SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_AUTO_5">A Rebel ship moves in to engage. You attempt to open communications, but realize the futility of that action when you see the ship is run by an AI. [ Auto SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_AUTO_6">This must be one of the Rebels' unmanned scout ships. Looks like there's no way around a fight. [ Auto SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_AUTO_7">Another unmanned ship patrols this area. You prepare the ship for combat. [ Auto SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_AUTO_8">This beacon is being patrolled by a unmanned scout. A fight is unavoidable. [ Auto SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_REBEL_AUTO_9">A small shuttle appears on the local radar. Turns out it is a Rebel automated scout! [ Auto SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_REBEL_1">This sector was bustling with activity just a few years ago. Now, more than half of the jump beacons have been destroyed, many settlements have been abandoned and the Rebels patrol constantly. [ 1-2 Stores, 1-2 Items, 6-8 Hostile, 1 Boarders, 1-2 Distress, 0-5 Nebula, 1-2 Empty, 0-2 Quests, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_REBEL_2">This sector was hit hard by the rebellion. The many alien settlements and stations located here are now watched over by almost an equal number of Rebel bases, heavy-handedly 'keeping the peace'. [ 1-2 Stores, 1-2 Items, 6-8 Hostile, 1 Boarders, 1-2 Distress, 0-5 Nebula, 1-2 Empty, 0-2 Quests, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_REBEL_3">Once the Federation forces were scattered, the Rebels came down hard on the locals here. Between the 'tax collectors' and military bases, the Rebel presence in this sector is high. [ 1-2 Stores, 1-2 Items, 6-8 Hostile, 1 Boarders, 1-2 Distress, 0-5 Nebula, 1-2 Empty, 0-2 Quests, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_REBEL_4">At one point this was one of the most commonly traveled sectors. Knowing that, the Rebels have stationed a number of fleets here. Be careful. [ 1-2 Stores, 1-2 Items, 6-8 Hostile, 1 Boarders, 1-2 Distress, 0-5 Nebula, 1-2 Empty, 0-2 Quests, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_REBEL_5">You will have to be very cautious in this sector. The Rebels have full control and are no doubt looking for you. [ 1-2 Stores, 1-2 Items, 6-8 Hostile, 1 Boarders, 1-2 Distress, 0-5 Nebula, 1-2 Empty, 0-2 Quests, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>

<!-- data/events_rock.xml -->
<text name="event_ROCK_ATHIEST_c1_choice">Tell them their god sent them here to join your crew. [ Rck SF DR S: 0.7, 3-4, RStuff ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_ATHIEST_c2_choice">Promise to share with them the truths they've been denied. [ RockCrew+ | x2 Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_ATHIEST_c3_choice">(Improved Sensors) Show them to your data suite. [ RockCrew+ ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_LOOTING_c1_choice">Strip the ship. [ LStd | LStd, Rck SF DR S: 0.7, 3-4, RStuff ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_LOOTING_c2_choice">Leave it alone. [ x2 Nil | LStd, Rck SF DR S: 0.7, 3-4, RStuff ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_LOOTING_c3_choice">(Slug Crew) Check for lifeforms and keep a lookout for ships while looting the wreck. [ LStd ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_MANTIS_FREIGHTER_c1_choice">Wait, then attack the surviving Mantis. [ Mts SF Enemy Weapons@2, K: MStd, CK: MStd | Mts SF K: MStd, CK: MStd ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_MANTIS_FREIGHTER_c2_choice">Ignore them. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_MANTIS_FREIGHTER_c3_choice">(Repair Drone) Repair the Rock ship. [ HStd, -1 Drone ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_MANTIS_FREIGHTER_c4_choice">(Hull Repair Drone) Repair their hull. [ -1 Drone, Mts SF K:MStd, CK: MStd ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_MANTIS_FREIGHTER_LIST_1_text">The Mantis craft are both too busy slaughtering one another to notice you. Eventually the smaller ship gets the upper hand, but they must have blown a fuse in the assault and their weapons system is inoperable. Now is the time to attack! [ Mts SF w/Enemy weapons@2 K: MStd, CK: MStd ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_MANTIS_FREIGHTER_LIST_2_text">The Mantis craft may have their differences, but when it comes to you they are of one mind. The smaller ship suffers a power failure as it moves to engage, but the larger one lets off a volley of fire and moves in to attack! [ Mts SF K: MStd, CK: MStd ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_MANTIS_HUNTER_c1_choice">Attack! [ Mts SF DR ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_MANTIS_HUNTER_c2_choice">Ignore them.  [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_MANTIS_HUNTER_c3_choice">(Rock Ship) Ram the bastards. [ Mts SF DR, Enemy engines@0 ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_MANTIS_HUNTER_c4_choice">(Rock Crew) Put your Rock crewmember on the comm. [ Mts SF DR ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_QUEST_MARRIAGE_START_c1_choice">Accept the passenger. [ Rock Marraige Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_QUEST_MARRIAGE_START_c2_choice">Refuse. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_QUEST_MARRIAGE_c1_c1_choice">Hand her over. [ Random Augment, LScrap ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_QUEST_MARRIAGE_c1_c2_choice">Refuse to comply. [ +1 Rock Crew, Rck SF K: MStd, CK: HStd ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_SHIP_SURRENDER_c1_choice">Accept their offer. [ RStuff ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_STARSHIP_MINE_c1_c1_choice">Send someone out there to defuse it. [ MScrap | [ MScrap | -6 Hull, Crew- (CB+) ] ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_STARSHIP_MINE_c1_c2_choice">(Missile Weapon) Attempt a controlled detonation using a missile. [ -4 Hull, -1 Miss, LScrap ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_STARSHIP_MINE_c1_c3_choice">(Beam Drone) Use a drone to cut away the mine with a precision beam. [ -1 Drone, LScrap ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_STARSHIP_MINE_c2_choice">(Improved Engines) Reverse thrusters! [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_UNLOCK1_c1_choice">"We're going to save them or die trying." [ Rock Homeworld Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_UNLOCK1_c2_choice">"We're strong enough to destroy you!" [ Rock Homeworld Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_UNLOCK1_c3_choice">Ignore them. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_ROCK_UNLOCK2_text">You arrive at the coordinates given and find yourself dangerously close to an M-class star! The other ship messages you, "Let's see how long your puny ship can handle this heat! Prepare for a challenge!" [ SF K: MStd, CK: HStd, Esc: Quest [ Rock Plating , +29 Hull ] ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_BOARDERS_ASTEROID_1">You arrive in an asteroid field and immediately begin evasive maneuvers when a loud clunk reverberates through the ship. At first you think the hull has been hit, but the noise came from some Rock intruders teleporting aboard the ship! [ Rck SF DR w/Asteroids, 1-2 Rock Boarders, S: 0.7, 3-4, RStuff ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_BOARDERS_ASTEROID_2">Your shields are being taxed as they deflect the debris from an asteroid field. As you weave your way between the rocks, you happen upon a Rock pirate stronghold. You register teleport signatures and hear shouts aboard the ship. [ Rck SF DR w/Asteroids, 1-2 Rock Boarders, S: 0.7, 3-4, RStuff ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_BOARDERS_SHIP_1">You passively scan a small Rock station that is next to the beacon. However they must not have appreciated your curiosity. A Rock ship pulls away from the station and you register an incoming teleporter signal as well! [ Rck SF DR, 1-3 Rock Boarders; S: 0.7, 3-4, RStuff ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_BOARDERS_SHIP_2">You find a Rock ship docked with a damaged Mantis fighter. Before you have a chance to hail them, the ship moves in to attack you and you register teleporter symbols from the disabled ship. They're using Mantis tech to board you! [ Rck SF DR, 1-3 Rock Boarders; S: 0.7, 3-4, RStuff ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_FIGHT_ASTEROID_1">A Rock mining vessel is harvesting the mineral-rich asteroids in this locality, and their scouts take your presence to be a transgression. Battle stations! [ Rck SF DR w/Asteroids S: 0.7, 3-4, RStuff ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_FIGHT_ASTEROID_2">A rookie Rock cargo ship has taken its orders too literally and took the most direct route to their destination... right through an asteroid field. They're confused and fire wildly as you jump in. [ Rck SF DR w/Asteroids S: 0.7, 3-4, RStuff ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_FIGHT_ASTEROID_3">The captain of a Rock freighter lost in the asteroid field hails you: "Our co-ordinates led us here, but only death greets us. What must be must be. Death to all." You power up the battle systems and wonder how long they've been stuck here. [ Rck SF DR w/Asteroids S: 0.7, 3-4, RStuff ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_PIRATE_ASTEROID_1">Minute fissures in the shields spark and crackle as the ship jumps into the wake of a huge asteroid. More asteroids follow, as does a lost and aggressive Rock pirate ship. [ PRck SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_PIRATE_ASTEROID_2">You exit the jump surrounded by dirt and rocks. Before long a blast is deflected by your shield, but that was no asteroid... Incoming pirate! [ PRck SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_PIRATE_SUN_1">Unusual solar activity in this region means you need to get out, quick. The Rock pirate nearby apparently thinks otherwise as they move to attack your ship. [ PRck SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_PIRATE_SUN_2">A Rock ship is silhouetted against a sun in supernova. They hail: "Even out here you follow us! We only wish to be left alone!" Out of panic or anger, they charge their weapons. [ PRck SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_PIRATE_1">As a naturally warlike species with few inter-galactic diplomatic ties, the Rock people have garnered quite a reputation as fearsome pirates. You stumble across one of their ships and they promptly live up to type. [ PRck SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_PIRATE_2">A Rock ship flies past your windows and you recognize outcast decorations on the hull. These must be pirates! [ PRck SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_PIRATE_3">A motley collection of Rock ships are stationed around this beacon - they look to have resorted to a pirate's life. Defensive maneuvers! [ PRck SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_PIRATE_4">As a naturally warlike species with few intergalactic diplomatic ties, the Rock people have garnered quite a reputation as fearsome pirates. You stumble across one of their ships and they promptly live up to type. [ PRck SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_SHIP_1">You encounter a Rock vessel and attempt to open trading frequencies, but they take it as an act of cultural transgression and open fire. [ Rck SF DR S: 0.7, 3-4, RStuff ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_SHIP_2">You jump into the middle of a Rock excavation project on a nearby moon. Unimpressed with your intrusion they move to defend themselves! [ Rck SF DR S: 0.7, 3-4, RStuff ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_SHIP_3">You intercept chatter from an approaching Rock ship: "Weapons, moving in to engage, arm the tubes." There is no talking to these guys. [ Rck SF DR S: 0.7, 3-4, RStuff ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_SHIP_4">As you jump in, a vast figure appears on the view-screen. The Rock captain rubs the green, moss-like appendage on his chin and then orders his crew to open fire. [ Rck SF DR S: 0.7, 3-4, RStuff ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_SHIP_5">It looks quiet, but you realize your computer is being scanned. A hidden Rock vessel hails you: "Why do you fill your computer with lies?! These are not the holy words!" Before you can interject they open fire. [ Rck SF DR S: 0.7, 3-4, RStuff ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_SHIP_6">You notice a Rock ship performing combat exercises. However, they quickly change their course to engage your ship. They apparently treat unregistered alien ships as handy target practice. [ Rck SF DR S: 0.7, 3-4, RStuff ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_SHIP_7">A loud 'thud' resounds through the ship after jump completion - you've just shunted a Rock fighter and he's already preparing to fire! [ Rck SF DR S: 0.7, 3-4, RStuff ]</text>
<text name="text_ROCK_SHIP_8">You're intercepted by a Rock salvage operation. They don't seem to mind that you're still on board while they junk your ship. [ Rck SF DR S: 0.7, 3-4, RStuff ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_ROCK_1">The Rock people have a particularly aggressive stance toward alien races trespassing in their space. You should tread carefully here. [ 2 Stores, 2-3 Empty, 1-2 Distress, 6-8 Hostile, 1-2 Boarders, 1-2 Items, 0-1 Quests, 7-8 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_ROCK_2">The Rock people are a powerful and proud race. It is not unheard of to have a peaceful journey through their lands, but don't count on it. [ 2 Stores, 2-3 Empty, 1-2 Distress, 6-8 Hostile, 1-2 Boarders, 1-2 Items, 0-1 Quests, 7-8 Neutral ]</text>

