<text name="event_BATTLEFIELD_INVESTIGAGE_5_c1_choice">Assist the survivor. [ More ... ]</text>
<text name="event_BATTLEFIELD_INVESTIGAGE_5_c2_choice">Leave the battlefield before other ships arrive. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_BATTLEFIELD_SURVIVOR_c1_choice">Make them comfortable for their final moments. [ Abadoth Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_BATTLEFIELD_SURVIVOR_c2_choice">(Advanced Medbay) Get them into the medbay! [ Crew+ ]</text>
<text name="event_BATTLEFIELD_SURVIVOR_c3_choice">(Clonebay) Try to clone them before it's too late. [ Crew+ ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_BATTLEFIELD_c1_c1_choice">Assist the survivor. [ More... ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_BATTLEFIELD_c1_c2_choice">Leave the battlefield before other ships arrive. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_BATTLEFIELD_c1_choice">(Slug Crew) Ask your Slug crew to scan for survivors. [ Abadoth Quest or BOs for Crew+ ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_BATTLEFIELD_c2_choice">Investigate the battlefield. [ -5 Hull | x3 Nil | [ Abadoth Quest or BOs for +1 Crew ] ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_CHOOSE_DEATH_c1_choice">Shields. [ Slg SF Shields@half K: MStd, CK: HStd ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_CHOOSE_DEATH_c2_choice">Oxygen. [ Slg SF Oxygen@half K: MStd, CK: MStd ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_CHOOSE_DEATH_c3_choice">Weapons. [ Slg SF Weapons@half K: HStd, CK: HStd ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_CHOOSE_DEATH_c4_choice">Offer 35 scrap to leave you alone. [ -35 Scrap ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_CHOOSE_DEATH_c5_choice">(Hacking System) Counter any hack attempt. [ Slg SF Hacking@0 K: HStd, CK: HStd ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_DOORS_c2_choice">(Hacking System) Counter the remote hacking. [ Slg SF Hacking@0, K: HStd, CK: HStd ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_DOORS_text">There are few more vicious beasts in the galaxy than a Slug with his back to the wall. The faltering ship armed with fire-weapons uses a remote hacking tool to try and disable your door system - they're going to burn you out! [ Slg SF Doors@0, K: MStd, CK: HStd ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_FAKE_STORE_c1_choice">Decline. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_FAKE_STORE_c2_c1_c1_choice">Understood. [ [ +5 Fuel, Store | Slg SF 1 Boarder, Weapons@0, K: HStd, CK: HStd | 2 Boarders, Slg SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ] or [ Nothing | 1 Boarder, Slg SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ] ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_FAKE_STORE_c2_c1_c1_c2_choice">Forget this. [ Nil | 1 Boarder, Slg SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_FAKE_STORE_c2_c1_c3_choice">(Slug crewmember) Our Slug senses someone aboard the ship. Investigate it. [ Slg SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_FAKE_STORE_c2_choice">Ask to see the goods. [ More ... ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_HULLFIX_c1_choice">No thanks. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_HULLFIX_c2_choice">Sure. [ Various Bad Things ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_HULLFIX_c3_choice">Ask if they would like payment. [ Slg SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 | Nil or +10 Hull for 50 Scrap ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_HULLFIX_REQUEST_1_c1_choice">Accept. [ -50 Scrap, +10 Hull ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_HULLFIX_REQUEST_1_c2_choice">Decline. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_HULLFIX_REQUEST_2_text">Just before the transmission is cut you hear, "They're not falling for it. Just kill the crew and we can ssstrip..." Looks like you're not getting out of here without a fight. [ Slg SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_MANTIS_text">The Mantis attack ship here looks to have been hunting Slugs on their home turf - a rare test of honor for the mightiest Mantis crews. Weapons up! [ Mts SF DR ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_MEDBAY_c2_choice">(Improved Medbay) Try to squeeze some extra power to the system. [ Slg SF Medbay@half, K: HStd, CK: HStd ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_MEDBAY_c3_choice">(Hacking System) Counter the remote hacking. [ Slg SF Hacking@0, K: HStd, CK: HStd ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_MEDBAY_text">A Slug ship hails you: "We've detected some worrying radiation coming from your medical unit, perhaps you should take a look?" As he signs off, your system shuts off and their crew teleports aboard from a nearby station. They don't look like engineers. [ Slg SF Clone/Medbay@0, K: HStd, CK: HStd ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_OXYGEN_c2_choice">(Improved Oxygen) Try to squeeze some extra power to the system. [ Slg SF Oxygen@half, K: MStd, CK: MStd ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_OXYGEN_c3_choice">(Hacking System) Counter the remote hacking. [ Slg SF Hacking@0, K: MStd, CK: MStd ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_OXYGEN_text">The Slugs here use a tactic you hoped you'd never see: they use a remote hacking satellite to sabotage your oxygen production system and then charge fire-weapons - you're going to suffocate! [ Slg SF Oxygen@0, K: MStd, CK: MStd ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_PIRATE_c1_choice">Attack! [ Prt SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_SLUG_PIRATE_c2_choice">Keep your distance and hope they haven't seen you yet. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_SLUG_PIRATE_TRAP_c1_choice">Tap their comm frequency. [ Slug Pirate Trap Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_SLUG_PIRATE_TRAP_c2_choice">Ignore them. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_SLUG_PIRATE_TRAP2_c1_c1_choice">Engage the pirate. [ Prt SF K: MStd, CK: HStd, S:HScrap ]</text>
<text name="event_QUEST_SLUG_PIRATE_TRAP2_c1_c2_choice">Head for the cache. [ Prt SF K: LStd, CK: MStd ]</text>
<text name="event_SECRET_WORD_ABADOTH_c1_choice">(Slug Crew) Ask your Slug crewmember to scan for life forms. [ MStd or Ztn SF DR ]</text>
<text name="event_SECRET_WORD_ABADOTH_c2_choice">Do a full system scan - though you're sure to lose some of your lead with the Rebels. [ Fleet+, MStd or Ztn SF DR ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_MANTIS_c1_choice">Attack the Mantis ship. [ Mts SF K: MStd, CK: MStd, DB: [ LScrapAugment | RStd ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_MANTIS_c2_choice">Attack the Slug ship. [ Slg SF K: HStd, CK: HStd ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_MANTIS_c3_choice">Of all the species in the galaxy, these two deserve one another. You power up the jump drive. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_PILOTING_c1_choice">Swear allegiance. [ Nil | SlugCrew+ ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_PILOTING_c2_choice">Never! [ Slg SF Engines@1, K: MStd, CK: HStd ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_PILOTING_c3_choice">(Improved Piloting) Override his control. [ Slg SF K: MStd, CK: HStd ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_PILOTING_c4_choice">(Hacking System) Counter the remote hacking. [ Slg SF Hacking@0, K: MStd, CK: HStd ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_RESCUE_c1_choice">Hire Slocknog. [ -55 Scrap, SlugCrew+ ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_RESCUE_c2_choice">Ignore Slocknog. [ SlugCrew+ or Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_ROCK_c1_choice">Engage the Slug ship. [ Slg SF K: MStd, CK: MStd, DB: [ x2 Nil | MStd ] ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_ROCK_c2_choice">Ignore them. [ x2 Nil | Rck SF DR; S: 0.7, 3-4, RStuff ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_TRICK_c1_choice">Send some crew to help. [ 1-3 Borders, Slg SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4; E: 0.5, 3-4 | Crew- (CB+), Slg SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4; E: 0.5, 3-4 | HScrap ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_TRICK_c2_choice">Ignore them. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DISTRESS_TRICK_c3_choice">(Mantis Crew) Have your Mantis oversee the repairs. [ HScrap ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DRINK_c1_choice">Drink. [ +10 Hull, Store | -25-35 Scrap ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DRINK_c2_choice">Refuse. [ Slg SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_DRINK_c3_choice">(Rock Crew) Have your Rockman pose as captain. [ Store, +10 Hull | Slg SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_FIGHT_text">It's rare for the Slugs to stay exposed in open space for long periods - the ship here may be lost, or just passing through, but either way he moves in to attack! [ Slg SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_MANTIS_text">You intercept comm chatter from an incoming Mantis ship. "Look. This ship appears not to be owned by the squishy ones. Maybe they won't smell so bad when we cut them open." They move in on your position. [ Mts SF DR ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_UNLOCK_SURRENDER_c1_choice">Let them live. [ [ HFuel | LStuff | MStuff ] | [ BioBeam or Slug Unlock Quest ] ]</text>
<text name="event_SLUG_SURRENDER_c1_choice">Let them live. [ [ HFuel | LStuff | MStuff ] | [ BioBeam or Slug Unlock Quest ] ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_SLUG_FIGHT_1">Your sensors are no match for the Slug's telepathic abilities - a ship you never even saw opens fire from astern! [ Slg SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_SLUG_FIGHT_2">The Slug vessel you encounter here has obviously made a big score and is looking to test its new armaments. They picked the wrong ship to attack. [ Slg SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_SLUG_FIGHT_3">A Slug passenger ship hails: "Please, your worthy alien highnessesss, we are unarmed and sseeking asssylum." You approach cautiously, and weapons immediately spring from their hull! [ Slg SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_SLUG_FIGHT_4">A Slug ship - a rogue, you suspect - approaches, but when he sees you're Federation he thinks better of the sneak attack and fires everything he has. [ Slg SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_NEBULA_SLUG_FIGHT_5">Direct attacks are not preferred by the Slugs, but of the three you see at this beacon, one has the brass to make a move on your position! [ Slg SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_SLUG_PIRATE_1">There appears to be a pirate ship nearby. Be on your guard; anyone trying to hunt in Slug territory is either formidable or deeply stupid, and in space, either can be dangerous. [ Prt SF DR; Sur: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_SLUG_PIRATE_2">"We knew anyone foolish enough to try and sneak through a Slug nebula would stick to open space. Yield your goods and we may let you live." You cut the transmission in lieu of a response. [ Prt SF DR; Sur: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_SLUG_PIRATE_3">Before you can take a moment's rest from the ever present nebulas in this sector, a pirate ship appears behind you and opens fire. [ Prt SF DR; Sur: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_SLUG_REBEL_1">As you arrive at the beacon, a hostile ship immediately registers on your scanners. You didn't expect to see Rebels extending their reach into Slug territory. Charge the weapons! [ Rbl SF DR; S: 0.5, 2-3, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_SLUG_REBEL_2">You jump into empty space and are relieved to see your sensors blink back to life. However, you are less pleased to see them immediately register a rebel ship on an approach vector! [ Rbl SF DR; S: 0.5, 2-3, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_SLUG_REBEL_3">You receive a message from a nearby ship, "Looks like our intelligence was correct! Sneaking through the clouds with the Slugs... No one can hide from the rebellion!" [ Rbl SF DR; S: 0.5, 2-3, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_SLUG_1">The only thing that can render a nebula more dangerous is if it's also home to the Slugs. This particular nebula is just that. [ 0-1 Non-Nebula Store, 2 Nebula Stores, 0-2 Items, 0-2 Non-Nebula Empty, 1-2 Non-Nebula Hostile, 3-4 Distress, 2-4 Empty Nebula, 5-7 Nebula Hostile, 1-3 IonStorm Slug Fights, 3-5 Neutral Nebula, 1-2 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_SLUG_2">This nebula is home to the telepathic Slugs. They'd sell their own slime for a crate of scrap, but they much prefer to just take it. [ 0-1 Non-Nebula Store, 2 Nebula Stores, 0-2 Items, 0-2 Non-Nebula Empty, 1-2 Non-Nebula Hostile, 3-4 Distress, 2-4 Empty Nebula, 5-7 Nebula Hostile, 1-3 IonStorm Slug Fights, 3-5 Neutral Nebula, 1-2 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_SLUG_3">You're told the Slug home world is somewhere in this nebula. You can't see them, but you know they're watching. [ 0-1 Non-Nebula Store, 2 Nebula Stores, 0-2 Items, 0-2 Non-Nebula Empty, 1-2 Non-Nebula Hostile, 3-4 Distress, 2-4 Empty Nebula, 5-7 Nebula Hostile, 1-3 IonStorm Slug Fights, 3-5 Neutral Nebula, 1-2 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_SLUG_4">The Slugs that live in this nebula field are a leisure-centered civilization. Everything in Slug life is done in the pursuit of more currency and more time in which to spend it on extravagant ventures. This, inevitably, leads to much treachery in open space. [ 0-1 Non-Nebula Store, 2 Nebula Stores, 0-2 Items, 0-2 Non-Nebula Empty, 1-2 Non-Nebula Hostile, 3-4 Distress, 2-4 Empty Nebula, 5-7 Nebula Hostile, 1-3 IonStorm Slug Fights, 3-5 Neutral Nebula, 1-2 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_SLUG_5">The Slugs developed on an ocean planet where the ability to telepathically sense another organism was more important than sight. Today they use this ability to navigate unfettered the depths of the nebulas they inhabit. [ 0-1 Non-Nebula Store, 2 Nebula Stores, 0-2 Items, 0-2 Non-Nebula Empty, 1-2 Non-Nebula Hostile, 3-4 Distress, 2-4 Empty Nebula, 5-7 Nebula Hostile, 1-3 IonStorm Slug Fights, 3-5 Neutral Nebula, 1-2 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_STORM_SLUG_FIGHT_1">The ion storm here threatens to deactivate your core systems, a fact made all the worse for the largely unaffected Slug ships circling like space-vultures. [ Slg SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_STORM_SLUG_FIGHT_2">The Slug ship that descends into view as you enter the ion storm must have sensed your distress - defensive action! [ Slg SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_STORM_SLUG_FIGHT_3">You arrive in the middle of an ion storm. Slugs generally avoid these storms but you find one waiting in ambush. Prepare for a fight! [ Slg SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_STORM_SLUG_FIGHT_4">You find yourself stuck in the middle of an ion storm with a Slug ship just a short distance away, refusing all hails. You cautiously try to slip further into the clouds, but they turn suddenly to attack! [ Slg SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4; Esc: 0.5, 3-4 ]</text>

<!-- data/events_zoltan.xml -->
<text name="event_NEBULA_ZOLTAN_EYE_c1_choice">Pull the ship in closer. [ Heal Bomb | Ztn SF DR | HScrap | Crew- (CB-) ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_ZOLTAN_EYE_c2_choice">Leave. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_NEBULA_ZOLTAN_ROCK_text">This nebula turns out to be the hiding place of a terrified rock crew taking refuge from the Zoltan border police. They don't seem prepared to risk your leaving with their co-ordinates, and open fire! [ Rck SF DR; S: 0.7, 3-4, RStuff ]</text>
<text name="event_STORM_ZOLTAN_SUPPLY_CHOICE_c1_choice">Secure the fuel supply. [ Prt SF K: LScrapFuel; CK: HScrapFuel; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_STORM_ZOLTAN_SUPPLY_CHOICE_c2_choice">Secure the ammunition. [ Prt SF K: LScrapMiss; CK: HScrapMissiles; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="event_STORM_ZOLTAN_SUPPLY_CHOICE_c3_choice">Let them leave. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_ASTEROID_text">You arrive in an asteroid field and are greeted by a Zoltan guard, "By attempting to access these closed mining fields, you are in violation of the Natural Mineral Protection Act. Your weaponry will be confiscated for processing." You don't have time for this. [ Ztn SF DR w/Asteroids ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_BOARDERS_text">There are few more zealous in their customs checks than the Zoltan. A team of border police beam on board. There's just a little confusion over your weapons licences, but things escalate rapidly from heated discussion to gunfire! [ Ztn SF DR 3-4 Zoltan Boarders ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_BOARDERS_MANTIS_text">The Mantis outcasts sometimes make the mistake of taking the Zoltan for easy game. A scout moves in to attack while a boarding party beams aboard from a nearby transport! [ Mts SF DR 2-3 Mantis Boarders ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_CREW_SCAN_c1_choice">You don't have time for this nonsense. Attack! [ Ztn SF DR ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_CREW_SCAN_c2_choice">Submit to profiling. [ Nil | [ Crew- (CB-) or [ Ztn SF 2-4 Zoltan Boarders, Weapons@half, K: LStd, CK: MStd ] ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_CREW_SCAN_c3_choice">(Slug Crew) Have your Slug talk them into letting you go. [ MFuel ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_CREW_SCAN_c4_choice">(Mind Control) Make the guards believe they have already checked your crew today. [ MFuel ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_DISTRESS_MANTIS_c1_choice">Interfere and save the Mantis ship. [ Ztn SF w/Asteroids K: LStd, CK: MStd ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_DISTRESS_MANTIS_c2_choice">Interfere and help the Zoltan ship. [ Mts SF w/Asteroids K: LStd, CK: MStd ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_DISTRESS_MANTIS_c3_choice">Don't interfere. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_ENGI_text">You jump into a debris field that used to be a Zoltan cruiser. Unfortunately, its Engi escort takes you for the attacker and retaliates! They refuse all hails. [ Eng SF DR ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_LIFERAFT_c1_choice">Engage the pirates. [ PZtn SF K: [ MStd, Trade -40 Scrap for Zoltan Crew ] CK: [ HScrapAugment ] ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_LIFERAFT_c2_choice">Leave. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_MANTIS_text">You pick up the last broadcast from a rupturing Zoltan freighter: "The Mantis, they're here, please-" You're interrupted by fire off the port bow! [ Mts SF DR ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_ODD_MOON_c1_choice">Check it out. [ Nil | LScrapWeapon | MScrap | -1 Mis [ RScrap | Nil | RScrapWeapon ] ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_ODD_MOON_c2_choice">Leave it be. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_ODD_MOON_c3_choice">(Boarding Drone) Send a drone to probe the surface. [ -1 Drone, ZoltanCrew+ ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_ODD_MOON_CHECK_4_c1_choice">Attempt to detonate some explosives to break through the surface. [ -1 Missile, [ Nil | LScrapWeapon | MScrap ] ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_ODD_MOON_CHECK_4_c2_choice">Explosives are too valuable to waste on excavation work. Let's get out of here. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_QUEST_PRIMITIVES_c1_c1_choice">Interfere - make first contact with the primitive aliens. [ Ztn SF K: LStd, CK: RStd ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_QUEST_PRIMITIVES_c1_c2_choice">Protect the aliens' way of life - Attack the Rebel ship. [ Rbl SF K: LScrapWeapon, CK: MScrapWeapon ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_QUEST_PRIMITIVES_c1_c3_choice">Leave. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_RIFT_FIGHT_c1_choice">Mantis. [ Mts SF K: LStd, CK: MStd, DB: HStd ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_RIFT_FIGHT_c2_choice">Slug. [ Slg SF K: LStd, CK: MStd, DB: HStd ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_RIFT_FIGHT_c3_choice">Rockmen. [ Rck SF K: LStd, CK: MStd, DB: HStd ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_SCIENCE_DOCK_c1_choice">Dock with them. [ MStuff | Ztn SF; S: 0.5, 3-4. [ LStd, ZoltanCrew+ ]; K: LStd; CK: MStd ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_SCIENCE_DOCK_c2_choice">Have them keep their distance. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_SCIENCE_DOCK_LIST_1_text">You allow them to approach, but are caught unaware when they open fire! [ Ztn SF S: [ 0.5, 3-4, LStd, ZoltanCrew+ ], K: LStd, CK: MStd ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_SURRENDER_c1_choice">Accept their offer. [ RStuff ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_TRADE_HUB_c1_choice">Try to talk your way in. [ Ztn SF DR, 2-4 Zoltan Boarders | [ Store | Primitives Quest ] ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_TRADE_HUB_c2_choice">(Teleporter) Beam directly to the civilian deck. [ Store | Primitives Quest ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_TRADE_HUB_c3_choice">(Zoltan Crew) Present his official documentation and pay the entry fee. [-10 Scrap, [ Store | Primitives Quest ] ]</text>
<text name="event_ZOLTAN_TRADE_HUB_c4_choice">Leave. [ Nil ]</text>
<text name="text_ZOLTAN_FIGHT_1">A Zoltan ship makes contact. "The nature of the day is rotational. The fever is emaciated. The reason is-" They've caught some nasty deep space dementia. Before you can consider finding help for them, they open fire. [ Ztn SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_ZOLTAN_FIGHT_2">You're surprised when a stationary Zoltan ship opens fire. It appears there are aggressive pugilists even among the 'enlightened'. [ Ztn SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_ZOLTAN_FIGHT_3">You receive a message, "This area is off limits. Submit your ship to processing." It's only one guard ship in a lonely beacon. You decide to fight your way out. [ Ztn SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_ZOLTAN_FIGHT_4">You discover a number of Zoltan civilian ships fighting off pirates. Unfortunately one ship mistakes your purpose and moves in to attack! They are refusing all communication; you have no choice but to fight. [ Ztn SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_ZOLTAN_FIGHT_5">Like many areas in Zoltan space, the residents of this sector prepared well for Galactic war. The military here seem to have given up reasoning with foreigners, preferring instead to attack on sight! [ Ztn SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_ZOLTAN_FIGHT_6">A Zoltan ship is waiting at this beacon. They request your identification, but radiation from the sun in this system is disrupting your communications. They take your silence for aggression and move in to attack. [ Ztn SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_ZOLTAN_FIGHT_7">The Zoltan ship patrolling this area hails you: "This area is off limits. Secrecy is vital." They power their weapons. [ Ztn SF DR ]</text>
<text name="text_ZOLTAN_PIRATE_1">"Emergency, all ships in range, we are under attack!" The frequency matches a nearby Zoltan ship; you move in on their pursuer. They take your intervention as a cue to jump away. Cowards. [ Prt SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_ZOLTAN_PIRATE_2">You jump just in time to witness a Zoltan ship's FTL drive overload. In his final moments their captain implores you not to get involved, but it's too late - their attacker is already upon you! [ Prt SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_ZOLTAN_PIRATE_3">Despite their precautions, pirates have begun to harass the local Zoltan settlements across this sector. One such pirate spots your ship and moves in to attack. [ Prt SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_ZOLTAN_PIRATE_4">A ship with pirate markings demands your surrender. These are sad times when even Zoltan space is beset by pirates. You doubt these fools will be missed. [ Prt SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_ZOLTAN_PIRATE_5">You spot a pirate ship looting a small Zoltan cruiser. They spot you and move in to attack before your FTL drive has a chance to recharge. [ Prt SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_ZOLTAN_PIRATE_6">You jump just in time to witness a Zoltan ship's FTL drive overload. In their final moments they implore you not to get involved, but it's too late - their attacker is already upon you! [ Prt SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_ZOLTAN_PIRATE_7">A ship with pirate markings demand that you surrender. These are sad times when even Zoltan space is beset by pirates. You doubt these fools will be missed. [ Prt SF DR; S: 0.5, 3-4, RStuff; Esc: 0.5, 2-4 ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_ZOLTAN_1">You've entered Zoltan territory. This species is not renowned for giving anything for nothing, but you can always be assured a fair hearing. [ 1 Zoltan Study, 2 Stores, 1-2 Empty, 1-2 Distress, 2-6 Nebula, 6-8 Hostile, 1-2 Boarders, 1-2 Items, 0-1 Quests, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_ZOLTAN_2">The Zoltan patrol their borders but let you pass when you ID as Federation. Let's hope they won't be so courteous to the Rebels. [ 1 Zoltan Study, 2 Stores, 1-2 Empty, 1-2 Distress, 2-6 Nebula, 6-8 Hostile, 1-2 Boarders, 1-2 Items, 0-1 Quests, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_ZOLTAN_3">You arrive in Zoltan space. From what you have heard they anticipated the coming war and made preparations to hold their borders. [ 1 Zoltan Study, 2 Stores, 1-2 Empty, 1-2 Distress, 2-6 Nebula, 6-8 Hostile, 1-2 Boarders, 1-2 Items, 0-1 Quests, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>
<text name="text_START_BEACON_ZOLTAN_4">You're far from Federation home space here in Zoltan territory, and it's not clear whether the authorities will have any goodwill remaining. Still, you have to push forward. [ 1 Zoltan Study, 2 Stores, 1-2 Empty, 1-2 Distress, 2-6 Nebula, 6-8 Hostile, 1-2 Boarders, 1-2 Items, 0-1 Quests, 5-6 Neutral ]</text>

